evant language, the experts should have a solid understanding of phytosanitary systems and terms and participate on an ongoing basis in the work of the panel. Working knowledge of other FAO languages (English, French, Spanish, Chinese, Arabic or Russian) should be indicated.</span></p> <p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN-CA\">Even if the selection occurs late, the selected experts should be available to attend the next meeting of the TPG in 15-19 October 2012, which can be found on the </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN-CA\"><a href=\"/calendar/date\">IPPC Calendar</a>.</span></p> <p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"></span></strong></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify; mso-outline-level: 1; tab-stops: 1.0cm;\">&nbsp;</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify; mso-outline-level: 1; tab-stops: 1.0cm;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; layout-grid-mode: line; color: #000000;\">Instructions for making nominations</span></span></strong></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify; tab-stops: 1.0cm;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; layout-grid-mode: line; color: #000000;\">For complete instructions, please refer to the call letter posted below. Nominations will be accepted from governments, National or Regional Plant Protection Organizations (NPPOs or RPPOs). Nominations should be submitted through the respective NPPO or RPPO Contact Point and self nominations should be supported by an accompanying letter from a government authority. </span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify; tab-stops: 1.0cm;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; layout-grid-mode: line; color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify; tab-stops: 1.0cm;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; layout-grid-mode: line; color: #000000;\">Submissions should be sent to the IPPC Secretariat by e-mail (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN-GB\"><a href=\"mailto:ippc@fao.org\"><span style=\"layout-grid-mode: line; mso-fareast-language: EN-US;\">ippc@fao.org</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; layout-grid-mode: line; color: #000000;\">) no later than <strong>31 August 2012</strong>. </span></p> <p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p> </span>&nbsp;</span></p> <p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','524'),(401,'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify; tab-stops: 0cm 17.0cm;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; layout-grid-mode: line; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-language: EN-US;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Nominations are being solicited by the Secretariat of the International Plant Protection Convention (IPPC) for authors of two IPPC diagnostic protocols, for <em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style: normal;\">Ips</em> spp. and <em style=\"mso-bidi-font-style: normal;\">Dendroctonus ponderosae</em>, as outlined below. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Nominations are due <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">1 November 2012</strong>.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; layout-grid-mode: line; color: black; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-language: EN-US;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"></span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 34.85pt 0pt 1cm; text-align: justify; tab-stops