 October 2009 will takes place in the PAKISTAN ROOM (A127 ext.56937/56936 Capacity. 44 with conference line).','9108'),(540,'<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">10 March 2010</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">Please find below the documents posted for this meeting. We have one more document that we will post as soon as it is ready.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">In addition, Bureau members are reminded to also bring the following documents:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">Report of the Buruea October 2009 meeting (</span><a href=\"https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=202500\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=202500</span></a><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">Report of the SPTA October 2009 meeting (</span><a href=\"https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=125447\" target=\"_BLANK\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=125447</span></a><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">&nbsp;)&nbsp;&nbsp;and <br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">all CPM-5 documents (</span><a href=\"https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=13330\" target=\"_BLANK\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=13330</span></a><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">),&nbsp;these will be the main documents for the meeting.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">Have a safe trip.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">Brent</span></p>','9131'),(541,'<p/>','9146'),(542,'<p/>','9178'),(543,'<p><strong>2011-03-09</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reloaded ISPM 15 report with shading</p>\r\n<p><strong>2011-03-08</strong></p>\r\n<p>- Updated:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Agenda</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>- New documents:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>documents list</li>\r\n<li>local information</li>\r\n<li>ISPM 15 symbol study</li>\r\n<li>Steward\'s review of member comments on draft ISPM Fruit Fly Trapping</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>2011-03-07</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Bureau will meet the 10th and 11th March 2011 to prepare and strategize for upcoming CPM-6 meeting.</p>\r\n<p>The Bureau will also meet again on the morning of the 18th March 2011 to recap the outcome of CPM-6 and prepare for the next Bureau meeting and the SPTA meeting.</p>\r\n<p>The Bureau meeting will start at 10:00 am on Thursday in the Canada roomC277<strong></strong>. Please stop by the Polish Bar on the way in as coffee will not be served in the meeting room.</p>\r\n<p>Have a safe trip.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','9195'),(544,'<p/>','9196'),(545,'<p/>','9197'),(546,'<p><strong>2012-03-14</strong></p>\r\n<p>A revised agenda and documents list will be posted today and hard copies distributed at the meeting.</p>\r\n<p>The Steward\'s summaries for member comments received 14 days prior to CPM-7 (2012) have been posted and hard copies will be distributed at the meeting:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Bur_2012_Mar_05:&nbsp;</strong>Steward&rsquo;s Summary for member comments received 14 days prior to CPM-7 (2012): Not widely distributed (supplement to ISPM 5: Glossary of phytosanitary terms) (2005-008)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Bur_2012_Mar_06:</strong>&nbsp;Steward&rsquo;s Summary for member comments received 14 days prior to CPM-7 (2012): Integrated measures for the production of plants for planting in international trade (2005-002)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Bur_2012_Mar_07:</strong>&nbsp;Steward&rsquo;s Summary for member comments received 14 days prior to CPM-7 (2012): Amendments to ISPM 5 (Glossary of phytosanitary terms) (1991-001)</li>\r\n<li><strong>Bur_2012_Mar_08:&nbsp;</strong>Steward&rsquo;s Summary for member comments received 14 days prior to CPM-7 (2012): Systems approaches for pest risk management of fruit flies (2004-022)&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">2012-03-12</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \">The Bureau meeting will start at 9:00 am on Thursday 15th March in the Canada room (C277). Please stop by the Polish Bar on the way in as coffee will not be served in the meeting room.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \">The purpose of this meeting is&nbsp;to prepare and strategize for the upcoming CPM-7 meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \">The Bureau will also meet again on Friday morning of the 23rd March 2012 to recap the outcome of CPM-7 and prepare for the next Bureau meetings and the SPTA meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \">The Secretariat has reviewed the CPM agenda and identified known issues that the Bureau will need to strategize for.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \"> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \">The following documents have been posted:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"line-height: normal; \">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; \"><strong>Bur_2012_Mar_01:&nbsp;</strong></span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; text-indent: -18pt; \">Agenda</span></li>\r\n<li><strong><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; \">Bur_2012_Mar_</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; text-indent: -18pt; \">02:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; text-indent: -18pt; \">Documents list</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \"><strong><span style=\"text-indent: 0px; \">Bur_2012_Mar_03:</span>&nbsp;</strong>Participants list</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \"><span style=\"text-indent: 0px; \"><strong>Bur_2012_Mar_04:</strong>&nbsp;</span>Local information</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \">Stewards of draft standards under the regular process will submit their recommendations on how to proceed with member comments; these will be distributed at the meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: black; font-family: \">Have a safe trip.</span></p>','9252'),(547,'<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><strong>2012-06-11:</strong></div>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\">A revised agenda and documents list will be posted today and hard copies distributed at the meeting.</p>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\">Documents 1 to 15 have been posted today.</p>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">The Bureau meeting will start at 10:00 am on Monday 18th&nbsp;June in the Canada room (C277). Please stop by the Polish Bar on the way in as coffee will not be served in the meeting room.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">Have a safe trip.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong>2012-06-15:</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\">Revised Agenda and Documents List have been updated to include <strong>documents from 16 to 20</strong> which have been posted today.</p>','9257'),(548,'<p/>','9266'),(549,'<p/>','9220'),(550,'<p/>','15618'),(551,'<p/>','20427'),(552,'<p/>','26946'),(553,'<p/>','27768'),(554,'<p/>','28182'),(555,'<p/><p></p>','9174'),(556,'<p/><p></p>','9268'),(557,'<p/><p/>','9269'),(558,'<p/><p/>','16593'),(559,'<p/><p/>','27000'),(560,'<p/><p/>','27907'),(561,'<p/><b>ISPM-6 SURVEY</b>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><b>Dear Contact Point,</b></span><span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The Implementation Review and Support System (IRSS) has been asked to conduct an exercise by the Standards Committee to identify challenges with implementation of ISPM6- Guidelines for Surveillance.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">In this respect, we are inviting you to complete this brief survey on ISPM6. ISPM6 is currently under review and we are trying to gather data on the challenges faced by countries to implement surveillance and the Standard.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The contributions you make to this survey will be invaluable and used as a basis for discussions in several regional workshops being planned for later this year and early next year. For more information on the workshops please see this link:&nbsp;<link ../index.php?id=1111050>https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=1111050</link>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Findings of this survey will be compiled and presented at CPM next year and will be submitted to the Review Group of the SC concerned with this ISPM6.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><b>We urge you to complete the survey by December 05, 2011.</b></span><span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Thank you for participating in this survey!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">The IPPC-IRSS Team.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">PS.&nbsp;&nbsp; A separate email containing the survey in Microsoft Word Format has been sent to you in the event you are unable to use this online tool. Please use one or the other.</span></p>','9228'),(562,'<p/>','9242'),(563,'<p/>','9185'),(564,'<p/>','9189'),(565,'<p/>','9243'),(566,'<p>This group purpose is to develop an Implementation review response every three years. The Implementation Review and Support System (IRSS) has been operational since April 2011. The Implementation Review Response will take the form of a triennial review report that will be based on:</p>\r\n<p>a. A summary report of the IPPC Help Desk activities</p>\r\n<p>b. A report on implementation difficulties from the Technical Consultation among RPPOs</p>\r\n<p>c. A summary report on implementation trends from the PCE</p>\r\n<p>d. The annual Secretariat IPP reports on the fulfilment of contracting reporting requirements</p>\r\n<p>e. Reports from other relevant international organizations.</p>\r\n<p>f. Generate action plans based on recommendations and needs identified</p>\r\n<p>On the basis of this response, recommendations for future activities to enhance implementation of the IPPC and ISPMs could be developed for incorporation into the CPM work programme. It will also expected to be a key input for the IPPC strategic and technical assistance planning. In addition, this response could address a number of recommendations of the report of the Independent Evaluation of the IPPC, specifically the review of the state of plant protection in the world and the development of procedures to monitor the implementation of standards.</p>','9250'),(567,'**Triennial Review Group - 1st Meeting (March 2012)**\r\n<p>This meeting is intended to set the stage for the development of the triennial report (implementation review response).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The members of the TRG are:</p>\r\n<p>1. Jane Chard - Chair of the Standards Committee.</p>\r\n<p>2. Lois Ransom - Chair of the Subsidiary Body on Dispute Settlement.</p>\r\n<p>3. Kyu-Ock Yim - Representative of the CPM Bureau.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.292969); -webkit-composition-fill-color: rgba(175, 192, 227, 0.230469); -webkit-composition-frame-color: rgba(77, 128, 180, 0.230469);\">4. Sheila Harvey - Representative of the Expert Working Group on Capacity Development.</span></p>\r\n<p>5. Technical leads from the IPPC Secretariat (Information Exchange, Standards Setting, Capacity Development and IRSS).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n ','9251'),(568,'This is a forum to support discussion on capacity development. Contributors include individuals who participated in the Expert Working Group on Capacity Development which took place in October 2010. The IPPC Secretariat will take the discussions on the forum into consideration when drafting papers for the CPM.','9160'),(569,'<p/>','9219'),(570,'	<table>\r\n				<tbody><tr class=\"tx-simplesurvey-pi1-listrow-header\">\r\n				<td><p><a href=\"index.php?id=workshops_on_draft_ispm_eval&amp;no_cache=1&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[test]=test&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[pointer]=0&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[sort]=title%3A1\">Title</a></p></td>\r\n				<td><p>Caption</p></td>\r\n				<!--td><p><a href=\"index.php?id=workshops_on_draft_ispm_eval&amp;no_cache=1&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[test]=test&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[pointer]=0&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[sort]=questions%3A1\" >Questions</a></p></td-->\r\n				<!--td><p>Results</p></td-->\r\n<td><p>Results</p></td>\r\n			</tr><tr>\r\n				<td valign=\"top\"><p><a href=\"index.php?id=workshops_on_draft_ispm_eval&amp;no_cache=1&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[showUid]=53&amp;cHash=0fce12389bc0efdd9ca6c38e6ecb5250\">REGIONAL WORKSHOP ON DRAFT ISPMS 2012</a></p></td>\r\n				<td valign=\"top\"><p>Participant Evaluation</p></td>\r\n				<!--td valign=\"top\"><p>99</p></td--><!--td valign=\"top\"><p><a href=\"index.php?id=workshops_on_draft_ispm_eval&amp;no_cache=1&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[showResult]=53\" >Show results</a></p></td--><td valign=\"top\"><p><a href=\"index.php?id=workshops_on_draft_ispm_eval&amp;no_cache=1&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[showResult2]=53\">Show Results