ults</a></p></td></tr><tr class=\"tx-simplesurvey-pi1-listrow-odd\">\r\n				<td valign=\"top\"><p><a href=\"index.php?id=workshops_on_draft_ispm_eval&amp;no_cache=1&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[showUid]=62&amp;cHash=94bef85d09d44cc6857dd0e70d2ad17f\">TALLER REGIONAL SOBRE PROYECTOS DE NIMF: CUESTIONARIO DE SEGUIMIENTO</a></p></td>\r\n				<td valign=\"top\"><p></p></td>\r\n				<!--td valign=\"top\"><p>7</p></td--><!--td valign=\"top\"><p><a href=\"index.php?id=workshops_on_draft_ispm_eval&amp;no_cache=1&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[showResult]=62\" >Show results</a></p></td--><td valign=\"top\"><p><a href=\"index.php?id=workshops_on_draft_ispm_eval&amp;no_cache=1&amp;tx_simplesurvey_pi1[showResult2]=62\">Show Results</a></p></td></tr>\r\n			</tbody></table>','9147'),(571,'<p>Subfoolders for meetings and <a href=\"index.php?id=204641&amp;no_cache=1&amp;L=0\">electronic decisions </a>are available through the righthand navigation menu.</p>','9014'),(572,'The draft ISPMs below have been approved by the Standards Committee to go for member consultation but due to resource constraints both within the Secretariat and with members they have not been selected by the Standards Committee to be part of the equivalent of 5 draft ISPMs sent for member consultation.\r\n\r\nThe Bureau (June 2010) requested the Secretariat to post these SC approved draft ISPMs on the IPP in the SC restricted work area and grant permission to CPM members to view them in advance of being circulated for a formal member consultation.\r\n\r\nNote: There are NO draft ISPMs at this moment approved by SC for member consultation.\r\n\r\n ','9151'),(573,'<p/>','9192'),(574,'<p><strong>2011-04-29</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We have finished posting documents for the SC meeting.&nbsp; We have revised the agenda and documents list, the agenda also  reflects other working group sessions we are proposing to deal with some  draft ISPMs and input for the Focus Group on improving the standard  setting process. We will hand out copies of all documents that have been posted or revised after Wednesday 27 April 2011, these will be handed out at the meeting.&nbsp; <br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> In discussion with the SC Chair we will make some minor schedule changes to accomodate Stewards, the main one affecting you will be on Monday afternoon,&nbsp; we will have a conference call with the Steward of the ISPM 15 Annex 1.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The meeting room will be open at 9:00 Monday morning and coffee and cornettos will be served at 9:30.&nbsp; Have a safe flight.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>- Brent Larson</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>2011-04-21</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We are in our final preparation for the upcoming SC, we will try to have most documents posted today but there are a few that will have to wait until next week as some are pending the outcome of some e-decisions by the SC.</li>\r\n<li>Due to a bug in Microsoft Word, the page numbering of Word documents &ldquo;Page X of Y&rdquo; does not up-date automatically. Before printing, double click on the footer and the page numbering will be up-dated. This must be done at each opening of the document.</li>\r\n<li>For our Wednesday evening, we are proposing a 1-1 &frac12; hour tour with an English mother-tongue licensed tour guide who will enlighten us about Rome while accompanying us to a typical Roman restaurant in the centre, about 2km from FAO. We are negotiating prices for the dinner and will let you know as soon as possible but the total price for this event is expected to be around &euro;45.  Could you please let Eva (Eva.Moller@fao.org) know if you are interested.</li>\r\n<li>Please note that on the occasion of the Pope John Paul II\'s beatification, the 1st May weekend will be expected to draw 2 million tourists and pilgrims to Rome. Rome\'s hotel availability will be thus seriously affected and we really hope you have already booked your hotel in advance as you were requested in the last SC update (20 March 2011).  If not, do it immediately, and if you are lucky to find accommodation for this period, please pay attention to the room prices, as in some cases they have doubled. Remember always to request for the FAO special room rate at least for those hotels surrounding the FAO area.</li>\r\n<li>PLEASE REMEMBER TO LOG ONTO THE IPP (https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=1110888 ) AND DOWNLOAD AND PRINT YOUR SC DOCUMENTS, no hard copies will be provided at the meeting.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;-Brent</p>\r\n<p><strong>2011-04-01</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> I will be posting a revised Agenda today.  These revisons reflect the outcome of CPM-6. The meeting times are indicated on the agenda and we propose to schedule the SC discussion following the agenda points.  We will cover agenda item 5.2 on Tuesday morning and we will have a demontration of the On Line Commenting system near the end of Wednesday afternoon\'s session. We also will have a cocktail on Monday night at 18:00 and a SC dinner on Wednesday night at 20:00. As there are several strategic discussion now on the agenda, SC members will be requested to work some evening sessions in small groups that will be arranged during the meeting. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Some more documents have been posted. Please note that we have posted revisons to the following docs:  - 17 - 2009-007 - 2009-003 We hope to have most of the remaining documents posted by 15 April 2011, however there are a couple of documents that will be posted late. - Brent Larson</li>\r\n</ul>','9193'),(575,'COMMISSION ON PHYTOSANITARY MEASURES\' STANDARDS COMMITTEE WORKING GROUP\r\n9-13 May 2011 Canada Room A357, FAO Headquarters, Rome, Italy\r\n9 May start time: 10:00 hrs\r\nDaily Schedule: 09:00-12:00 and 13:30-16:30\r\nGreetings everyone. All of the meeting documents have been posted. Please let me know if you need anything before the meeting.\r\nStephanie Dubon (stephanie.dubon@fao.org)','9194'),(576,'**2 August 2011**\r\n\r\nThe 2011 November SC meeting will be held 7-11 November at FAO Headquarters in Rome, Italy.\r\n\r\nPlease review the two draft ISPMs posted below (2005-002 Plants for Planting and 2004-022 Fruit Fly Systems Approach) in preparation for the meeting. NPPOs and RPPOs should submit all comments to the IPPC Secretariat at ippc@fao.org before 30 September 2011.','9222'),(577,'<p/>','9240'),(578,'<p><strong>2012-04-20</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dear SC members, we realized that some images in the draft DP for Tilletia indica were not visible and we have therefore posted a new version today.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2012-04-13</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\">Dear SC members,</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \">Please ensure you participate in the SC forum to help us set priorities of the agenda (</span><a style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \" href=\"index.php?id=1110885&amp;no_cache=1&amp;L=0&amp;view=single_thread&amp;cat_uid=19&amp;conf_uid=27&amp;thread_uid=93\">https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=1110885&amp;no_cache=1&amp;L=0&amp;view=single_thread&amp;cat_uid=19&amp;conf_uid=27&amp;thread_uid=93</a><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \"> ), even if you do not have a suggestion, please indicate this</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \">remember that </span><strong style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \"><em><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">NO PRINTED COPIES</span></em></strong><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \"> of SC documents will be provided by the Secretariat</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \">five draft ISPMs (agenda 5) have been posted on the OCS (ocs.ippc.int)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \">today is the final day for posting SC documents on the IPP, no more documents will be posted until the meeting starts on Monday 23 April 2012</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \">when viewing documents in the SC restricted work area of the IPP (</span><a style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \" href=\"index.php?id=1111076\">https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=1111076</a><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \"> ), in order to see all the SC documents, click the &ldquo;All&rdquo; button under the table on the left hand corner- this will also allow you to sort your documents by agenda, document number, posted date, etc clicking the header arrow</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \">the document on the e-decisions, agenda 4.2 will be finalized after the forum is closed</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \">the SC dinner has been moved to Tuesday night due to an Italian holiday on Wednesday</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \">the Secretariat is developing a &ldquo;New SC member guide&rdquo; and will be setting up interview appointments with several of you</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt; \">some lunch hour sessions will be set up to demonstrate the Online Glossary, the OCS and the IPP</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Monday morning 23 April 2012</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: -24px;\"><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt;\">please pick up your FAO building passes early, opens at 8:30</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt;\">the German Room (C269) will be open at 9:00</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt;\">we will be following the UN conference services seating plan and request SC members not to move their name plates</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt;\">coffee and pastries will be served at 9:30</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-indent: -18pt;\">DSA will be distributed Monday during the meeting</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&lt;!--[if !supportLists]--&gt;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>2012-04-05</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">CPM-7 (2012) is over and we continue to prepare for the April SC and SC-7 meetings.&nbsp; Invitations have gone out for the SC and SC-7 (we still do not have a confirmed SC-7 member from Africa).&nbsp; I hope that you have all initiated your travel plans including visa applications and requests for funding if needed.&nbsp; As our funding for SC travel comes from a trust fund, the funding is linked to attendance at the SC meeting and we are unable to assist&nbsp;SC members who only wish to attend part of the 5 day meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">A e-discussion was initiated today to determine necessary detail for SC discussion for each agenda item, <a href=\"index.php?id=1110885&amp;no_cache=1&amp;L=0&amp;view=single_thread&amp;cat_uid=19&amp;conf_uid=27&amp;thread_uid=93\">click here</a>.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\"><strong>Documents:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">As this is the first time to use the OCS for posting draft ISPMs, we have had a technical difficulties and we thank you for your patience as we have tried to accommodate those with problems.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">Today we have posted a revised Agenda, Documents list and Participants list as well as several new documents (see posting date below). </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">All documents related to draft ISPMs have now been posted on the OCS or in the SC-7 restricted work area or DP queued area.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Links are provided in the Agenda.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">13 April 2012 will be our last day for posting documents in the SC restricted work area of the IPP (below) <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>and we still have a few documents to post next week on the following agenda items: </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt 42pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 9.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7pt \">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">3.1, CPM-7 follow up (excerpts from the draft CPM-7 report, Cold Treatment Formal Objections and&nbsp;the List of topics),</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt 42pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 9.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7pt \">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">3.2, IRSS and Regional Workshops for 2012 </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt 42pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 9.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7pt \">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">4.2, e-decisions</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt 42pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 9.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7pt \">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">4.3, EWG updates</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt 42pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 9.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7pt \">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; color: #000000;\">9, TP updates</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>2012-03-13</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Once CPM-7 (2012) confirms the SC membership we will send out invitations to new members.<br /></span><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;<br /></span></strong><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">We have extended the deadline for submitting discussion papers to the Secretariat from 15 March 2012 to 2 April 2012.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The Secretariat will process these papers and post them on the IPP during the week of 9 to 13 April 2012.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>If any documents are processed later than the 13 April 2012 we will distribute hard copies at the beginning of the meeting.<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The Agenda (containing links to many documents) and other meeting documents are now posted below.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Draft ISPMs have been uploaded into the OCS where SC members can log in to view, download and/or print the them (follow link on the agenda).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>We have done this to give SC members some exposure to the OCS and it saves the Secretariat time in formatting the drafts. If you have any problem viewing the OCS, please e-mail Stephanie Dubon (</span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Times New Roman;\"><a href=\"mailto:Stephanie.Dubon@fao.org\">Stephanie.Dubon@fao.org</a></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;<br /></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">There is also a link to a draft standard (revision of Annex 1 to ISPM15) in the SC-7 restricted work area. The SC needs to consider the CPM-7 (2012) decision and decide to sent this to the SC-7 for review, send it for a second member consultation or put it on hold.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;<br /></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">As we have so many new SC members coming on board, we have arranged a special dinner for the Wednesday night of the meeting, make sure to keep that open.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>2012-02-10</strong></p>\r\n<p>We will be sending out the generic letter of invite shortly, as we have 15 member with their terms ending at CPM-7 (2012), it is impossible to send out individual letters of invite until the CPM confirms the SC membership.&nbsp; This also means we have very little time to prepare and make travel arrangements so SC members will have to act immediately after CPM-7 and timelines will be tight to make travel arrangements and get visas. We appreciate your speedy cooperation.</p>\r\n<p>We hope to have all the draft ISPMs posted below in the first week of March 2012. This year we may have to post some draft ISPMs later including:<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; the proposal for the Dieletric Heat: Phytosanitary Treatment, <br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; the revisions to ISPM 15- Annex 1 and <br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; the criteria for new treatments to be included in ISPM 15.</p>\r\n<p>After we have most of our drafts posted, the SC Chair would like to open a forum discussion (e-decision) to obtain the views of SC members on the priority for reviewing draft standards and help determine a more manageable agenda.</p>','9241'),(579,'**2012-05-08**\r\n\r\nThe Secretariat has posted all the meeting documents below. Please contact Stephanie.Dubon@fao.org should you have any questions.','9247'),(580,'<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><br /></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><strong>11 November 2012</strong></div>\r\n<p class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\">We posted on 9 November a <strong>new document and revised 3 other documents:</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11px;\"> </span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt;\">\r\n<li>New document : SC_2012_Nov_31 (ePhyto update for agenda item 3.3)</li>\r\n<li>Revised document (SC_2012_Nov_17_Rev1: Update of polls and forums discussed on the e-decision site), revised in order to take into account the results of the last SC e-decision (for the selection of experts for the Technical Panel on Phytosanitary treatments) which closed last Tuesday.</li>\r\n<li>Revised version of the agenda: SC_2012_Nov_01</li>\r\n<li>Revised version of the documents list: SC_2012_Nov_02</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>We will print copies&nbsp;</strong></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>and they will be available for</strong></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>&nbsp;all of you on Monday morning</strong></span><strong>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Also, concerning the items 5.1 and 5.2 of the agenda, we noticed that the two draft ISPMs that went out for substantial concerns commenting period this summer and were posted on the OCS from 15 May 2012 had recently disappeared from the OCS :</p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt;\">\r\n<li>2006-001:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://faohqmail.fao.org/owa/redir.aspx?C=1GRasxLqVESXOu1mllD4KkzfCc-Nk89IsYIfpyOkIteTl2NOQ4ZrS1QZRCbKhZCIJVK5t5uTy1M.&amp;URL=https%3a%2f%2fwww.ippc.int%2findex.php%3fid%3d1111142%26tx_publication_pi1%255bshowUid%255d%3d2185132%26frompage%3d1111142%26type%3dpublication%26subtype%3d%26L%3d0\" target=\"_blank\">Draft revision of Annex 1 (approved treatments associated with wood packaging material) to ISPM 15:2009&nbsp;</a>:&nbsp; item 5.1 on the agenda</li>\r\n<li>2005-001: Draft&nbsp;<a href=\"https://faohqmail.fao.org/owa/redir.aspx?C=1GRasxLqVESXOu1mllD4KkzfCc-Nk89IsYIfpyOkIteTl2NOQ4ZrS1QZRCbKhZCIJVK5t5uTy1M.&amp;URL=https%3a%2f%2fwww.ippc.int%2findex.php%3fid%3d1111142%26tx_publication_pi1%255bshowUid%255d%3d2185134%26frompage%3d1111142%26type%3dpublication%26subtype%3d%26L%3d0\" target=\"_blank\">Annex (Pest risk analysis for plants as quarantine pests) to ISPM 11:2004:</a>&nbsp;item 5.2 on the agenda</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>We would like to apologize for this problem, due to some unknown reason, and we are trying to fix this on the OCS as soon as possible.</div>\r\n<div>As an immediate solution,&nbsp;<strong>w</strong><strong>e have also posted these draft ISPMs (word file</strong><strong>s</strong><strong>) directly in this page</strong>&nbsp;so that all of you can still have access and download these documents.</div>\r\n<div>Please also note that we have done the same thing for the two other draft ISPMs that will be discussed at the SC meeting under agenda items 6.1 (2006-029: international movement of wood) and 6.2 (2008-001: sea containers).</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><br /></p>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><strong>26 October 2012<span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">Today was officially the last day for posting documents and we are therefore pleased to have posted a number of new documents as well as</span><strong style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">a recent version of the agenda and the documents list.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\">\r\n<div style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Consolas, monospace; font-size: x-small;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Consolas, monospace;\">W</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">hen viewing documents in the SC restricted work area, in order to see all the SC documents, click the &ldquo;All&rdquo; button under the table on the left hand corner.&nbsp; Then you will be able to sort your documents by agenda, document number, posted date, etc by clicking the header arrow.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></div>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">Please note that in total four draft ISPMs (agenda items 5 and 6) have been posted on the OCS (</span><a style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\" href=\"https://faohqmail.fao.org/owa/redir.aspx?C=7C0tc9raRUKDOg49kBEp66tOVmo6h89ICRQT6p3-DTmLOSUuCQycT5qNVRbK_VaDWBMLYa2GmaU.&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2focs.ippc.int\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">http://ocs.ippc.int</span></span></a><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">). You have to scroll down the menu to see all of them.</span><br /><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">Remember that for all the documents that have been posted today and before:</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: small; color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>NO PRINTED COPIES</strong></em></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">of SC documents will be provided by the Secretariat.</span><br /></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><br /></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">One working paper is still missing and is marked SC_2012_Nov_XX on the agenda. For this paper, we will hand out printed copies on the first day of the meeting.</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><br /></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><br /></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><br /></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><strong>10 October 2012</strong></div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\">Several documents have been posted, hereunder, the documents list, the participants list and the draft specifications together with compiled comments from MC on draft specifications.</div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><strong>Note also that the draft ISPM on <em>Miminizing pest movement in by sea containers and conveyances in international trade</em> has been posted in the OCS</strong> to ensure that all contact points can view the draft (after log on).</div>\r\n<div class=\"csc-header csc-header-n1\"><img class=\"spacer-gif\" src=\"clear.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"5\" /><br /></div>\r\n<!--  Header: [end] --><!--  Image block: [begin] --><!--  Text: [begin] -->\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\"><strong>11 September 2012</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\">The 2012 November SC meeting will be held 12-16 November 2012 at FAO Headquarters in Rome, Italy.</p>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\">Two draft ISPMs have been posted on the Online Comment System (<span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: \"><a href=\"http://ocs.ippc.int/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">ocs.ippc.int/index.html</a>): </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\">Please make sure to download these, we have a new <span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Substantial Concerns Commenting Period (SCCP) on draft ISPMs </span>where&nbsp;NPPOs and&nbsp;RPPOs may&nbsp;submit their&nbsp;comments before 30 September 2011. Compiled comments will be forwarded to the stewards during the first week of October 2012 and we hope to have the compiled comments with the steward\'s responses posted by the end of October 2012.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Draft Annex to ISPM 11: Pest risk analysis for plants as quarantine pests (2005-001)</li>\r\n<li>Draft revision of Annex 1 to ISPM 15: Approved treatments associated with wood packaging material (2006-011)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\">Please check the SC restricted work area as we post new documents.</p>\r\n<p>The deadline to have your documents into the Secretariat is <strong>8 October 2012</strong> and all documents should be posted by&nbsp;<strong>26 October 2012.<br /></strong></p>','9262'),(581,'<!--p>This page provides access to a forum and a tool for conducting polls to enable the SC to conduct discussions and make decisions by electronic means. For more information on the electronic decision making process, refer to the excerpt from the SC report (November 2010) click <strong><a href=\"/node/9176\">here</a></strong> to open.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Polls</strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"border: 1px solid #000;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Title</td>\r\n<td>Caption</td>\r\n<td>Results</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href=\"/polls/2013escnov16-adoption-international-standards-diagnostic-protocol-tilletia-indica-mitra-2004\">2013_eSC_Nov_16: Adoption of international standards: Diagnostic protocol for Tilletia indica Mitra (2004-014) as Annex XX to ISPM 27 (2004-014)</a></td>\r\n<td>OPEN</td>\r\n<td><a href=\"/node/27026/votes\">Show Results</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href=\"/polls/poll-diagnostic-protocol-phyllosticta-citricarpa-mcalpine-aa-fruits-2004-023-annex-ispm-27\">Poll: the diagnostic protocol for Phyllosticta citricarpa (McAlpine) Aa on fruits (2004-023), as an annex to ISPM 27: 2006 (2013_eSC_Nov_13_Phyllosticta)</a></td>\r\n<td>CLOSED</td>\r\n<td><a href=\"/node/27004/votes\">Show Results</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table-->\r\n<p><strong>FORUM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Click <strong><a href=\"/forum/category/discussions-between-june-2014-november-2014/\">here</a></strong>&nbsp;to go the the discussion forum.</p>\r\n<p>Discussion forum&#39;s instructions: This is a forum to support electronic decision-making by the SC on issues where discussion is required.\r\n <ul><li> You must be logged in to the IPPC website to access the forum. The forum is only accessible to members of the SC. </li>\r\n <li>On the homepage, near the top, click the tab labelled &quot;Forums&quot;, and then scroll \r\n down the forums page until you see &quot;SC forum&quot;. Click on the most recent discussions and choose a topic to comment on. </li>\r\n <li>Visit the discussion forum on a regular basis. New discussion topics will be opened regularly, and they will have specific deadlines for your response. </li>\r\n <li>To respond to a post and provide input on an issue, simply scroll to the bottom of the thread and enter your text into the message window. Click &quot;Preview&quot; to see your post before it is added to the site. Once you are satisfied with your response, click &quot;Post&quot; to add it to the discussion. </li>\r\n <li>To be alerted when there is new activity on a topic, simply check the box beside &quot;Notify me when new comments are posted&quot; near the bottom of a topic page. An email will be sent to you when new threads and responses to threads are posted. </li>\r\n <li>If you no longer wish to receive emails when new posts are added to the forum, simply unclick the box beside &quot;Notify me when new comments are posted&quot;. </li>\r\n </ul>\r\n The IPPC Frequently asked questions page provides answers to some general questions about the IPPC website (e.g. how to change your password) are available: <a href=\"https://www.ippc.int/faq/\">https://www.ippc.int/faq/</a>.</p>\r\n \r\n <p>For specific questions or suggestions about how to use this tool, contact the Secretariat (ippc@fao.org).</p><p><strong>Support documents for e-decisions</strong></p><p><strong><em>Please remember there may be more than 10 documents posted below. To view more than 10 documents, please click the &quot;All&quot; button under the Publication table.</em></strong></p>','9086'),(582,'The IPPC Standards Committee (SC) has, for some years now, been discussing issues and making decisions intersessionally between face-to-face SC meetings  using electronic media. The SC has recently begun using webpages on the IPP (rather than email) to make decisions electronically.\r\n\r\nThe SC agreed at its November 2010 meeting to support the Secretariat in its development of an enhanced mechanism for implementing the SC\'s procedures for making electronic decisions (see below for a copy of the procedures which were consolidated at the SC meeting in November 2010).\r\n\r\nPublications attached to this page include excerpts from SC meeting reports that summarise, and are relevant to, e-decisions made by the SC.','9176'),(585,'<p/>','9090'),(586,'<p/>','9259'),(587,'<p/>','15292'),(588,'<h1>Archived Discussion forum for electronic decision-making by SC</h1>\r\n<table>\r\n	<tr> \r\n		<th>Discussion Categories</th>\r\n		<th>Discussion Threads</th>\r\n		<th>Posts</th>\r\n		<th>Last Post Info</th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr class=\"odd\">\r\n		<td>\r\n		<dl>\r\n		<dt><strong><a href=\"/node/15295\">Discussions between May 2012 and Nov 2012</a></strong></dt>\r\n		<dd></dd>\r\n		<dd></dd>\r\n		</dl>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>8</td>\r\n		<td>105</td>\r\n		<td>Oct 25 2012, 11 46 PM<br>In: <strong>Closed: </strong>2012_eSC_Nov_08: E-decision for the selection of e...<br>By: Ana Lilia Montealegre Lara<br></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n\r\n</table>\r\n<table   border=1 >\r\n		<tr>\r\n				<td><p>Title</p></td>\r\n				<td><p>Caption</p></td>\r\n				<td><p>Results</p></td>\r\n			</tr><tr>	<td valign=\"top\"><p><a href=\"/node/15294\">Poll: SC decision to select experts for the TPPT</a></p></td>\r\n				<td valign=\"top\"><p>CLOSED</p></td>\r\n				<td valign=\"top\"><p><a href=\"/node/15294#results\">Show Results</a>\r\n</tr><tr class=\"tx-simplesurvey-pi1-listrow-odd\">\r\n				<td valign=\"top\"><p><a href=\"/node/15296\">Poll: SC decision to select an ex