 <td class=\"views-field views-field-active\" >\r\n            CLOSED          </td>\r\n                  <td class=\"views-field views-field-nothing\" >\r\n            <a href=\"/node/27756/votes\">Show results</a>          </td>\r\n              </tr>\r\n      </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n','28184'),(595,'<p/>','14576'),(596,'**7 May 2013**\r\n\r\nWe would like to inform you that SC documents 37 to 40 were posted today.\r\n\r\n\r\n**3 May 2013**\r\n\r\nWe would like to inform you that a new SC document is now available on the Steward\'s comments on the international movement of grain, submitted by Jens Unger today (SC_2013_May_36). The Provisional agenda and Documents list were updated accordingly. All documents posted after the 26 April will be printed and distributed on the first day of the meeting.\r\n\r\n**2 May 2013**\r\n\r\nWe would like to inform you that the SC document on the Update on activities of the TPPT (SC_2013_May_34) has been modified to correct an error in the header of the document. The header of the previous version included the incorrect document and agenda numbers. The revised version has been posted on the IPP.\r\n\r\nWe apologize for any inconvenience.\r\n\r\n**26 April 2013**\r\n\r\nAs indicated yesterday, we posted today the 2012 November TPDP meeting report and the 2013 February TPDP Virtual meeting report, together with a revised document list.\r\n\r\nThank you for your patience, all documents for the 2013 May SC are now posted.\r\n\r\nLooking forward to seeing you on the 6th May.\r\n\r\n**25 April 2013**\r\n\r\nWe would like to inform you that **we posted today all remaining documents**  for the May Standards Committee (SC) meeting (6-10 May 2013) (including a revised version of the agenda, the documents list and the participants list).\r\n\r\nWe would like to apologize for the small delay as we first intended to have everything posted by 24 April.\r\n\r\n**The only missing documents are the 2012 November TPDP meeting report and the 2013 February TPDP Virtual meeting report, which will be posted tomorrow.**\r\n\r\nWhen viewing documents in the SC restricted work area, in order to see all the SC documents, click the “All” button under the table on the left hand corner. \r\n\r\nThen you  will be able to sort your documents by agenda number, document number, posted date, etc by clicking the header arrow.\r\n\r\nRemember that for all the documents that have been posted today and before: ***NO PRINTED COPIES***  of SC documents will be provided by the Secretariat.\r\n\r\nAlso we would like to inform you that, regarding the draft specification on the *International movement of grain*, CPM-8 (2013) agreed that the Secretariat in consultation with the SC Chair could decide to invite experts with experience in strategic matters to participate in the 2013 May SC meeting. We tried to do that but, due to the short period of time between CPM8 and the May SC, we were unable to invite these experts. However, we received some comments from contracting parties on this issue and prepared a SC paper with these comments (SC_2013_May_29).\r\n\r\nPlease also note for Monday morning 6 May 2013:\r\n\r\nPlease pick up your FAO building passes early, the pass office opens at 8:30\r\nThe German Room (C269) will be open at 9:00\r\nWe will be following the UN conference services seating plan and request SC members not to move their name plates\r\nCoffee and pastries will be served at 9:30 in front of the meeting room\r\nThose who will receive DSA will have to collect them at the Banca Intesa (inside FAO building). We will give you more details later.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nAlso we will be experiencing a different set for the cocktail on Monday evening (18:30). We will be providing drinks and a few snacks, but **we would be grateful if you could also bring a few snacks from your respective countries**, so that we could have some international diversity ! Thank you in advance for that.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**16 April 2013**\r\n\r\nWe have posted today new working papers, including:\r\n\r\n- revised versions of the agenda and the document list\r\n- the draft specification for the revision of ISPM 6 (2009-004)\r\n- paper on guidelines on the role of lead and assistant steward(s)\r\n- paper on explanatory documents\r\n- SC-7 membership list\r\n- update on polls and forums discussed on the e-decision site\r\n- paper on the selection of equivalent of five drafts for 2013 member consultation\r\n- Update on the activities of the TPFQ\r\n\r\nPlease note that our final date for posting documents for the 2013 May SC meeting will be **24 April** (taking into account the short period between CPM-8 and the SC).\r\n\r\n**28 March 2013**\r\n\r\nWe have posted new working papers, including a revised version of the agenda, the document list and the participants list.\r\n\r\nWe will be posting more papers next week, so please check the SC restricted work area.\r\n\r\n***Please remember that to view more than 10 documents, you should click the \"All\" button under the Publication table.***\r\n\r\n**21 March 2013**\r\n\r\nThe draft Amendments to ISPM 5 and the draft ISPM on Sea containers have now been posted, so all draft ISPMs presented to the 2013 May SC are now posted. Please note that a paper with Steward\'s notes has been posted together with the draft ISPM on Sea containers.\r\n\r\nWe intend to post other working papers in the next days together with a revision of the provisional agenda.\r\n\r\n**28 February 2013**\r\n\r\nThe 2013 May SC meeting will be held on 6-10 May 2013 at FAO Headquarters in Rome, Italy.\r\n\r\nPlease note that **22 March** is the deadline for registering to the meeting, submitting requests for funding and submitting any discussion paper to the Secretariat.\r\n\r\nWe have just posted below a first version of the provisional agenda together with 4 draft ISPMs (International movement of wood, Movement of growing media, Phytosanitary procedures for fruit fly management, phytosanitary pre-clearance) and a draft specification (Import permits). We will post as soon as possible the remaining ISPMs which are on the agenda (Sea containers, Amendments to ISPM 5). Other meeting documents will be posted in the next weeks. We intend to have all documents posted by **24 April**.\r\n\r\nSo please check the SC restricted work area as we post new documents.\r\n\r\nPlease also note that we have scheduled to open mid-March a forum discussion (e-decision) to obtain the views of SC members on the order of the agenda (priority for reviewing draft standards).\r\n\r\nThanks for your cooperation.','14577'),(597,'**Dear Standards Committee member working group (SC-7), Welcome.**\r\n\r\nThe SC-7 2013 will be from May 13 to May 17. We will start the meeting at 10:00 on Monday (13 May).\r\n\r\nThe meeting will be held on Canada Room (A356/7) at FAO Headquarters, Rome, Italy.\r\n\r\nSee you all in May 2013.\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\nIPPC Standards Setting Secretariat.\r\n\r\n**Obs.**: Please remember there are more than 10 documents posted. To view more than 10 documents, please click the \"All\" button under the Publication table.\r\n\r\nNo printed documents will be distributed. Please, bring all the documents with you.\r\n\r\n******************************\r\n\r\n**2013-04-16**: Participants list posted.\r\n\r\n**2013-03-20**: All documents (but for the Participants list) have now been posted.\r\n\r\n**2013-03-04**: We have reposted the draft ISPM on Electronic certification because the steward incorporated TPG recommendations. We have also posted documents 2 and 4-10 today.\r\n\r\n**2013-02-28**: We have started posting documents for the SC-7 May 2013 meeting. Please check this space regularly for new documents.','14578'),(598,'**05 November**\r\n\r\nPlease note that a revised version of the document 27 was posted today (with one attachment, Attachment 23).\r\n\r\n- 27_SC_2013_Nov_Rev1: Recommendations Call for topics  \r\n- Also, a revised version of the the documents list reflecting this modification. \r\n\r\n\r\n**31 October**\r\n\r\nWe would like to inform you that we posted today all remaining documents for the 18-22 November SC meeting:  \r\n- 38_SC_2013_Nov: Update on polls and forums discussed on e-decision site  \r\n- 39_SC_2013_Nov: Items arising from CPM Bureau  \r\n- 40_SC_2013_Nov: NRO update  \r\n- 41_SC_2013_Nov: SPG update  \r\n- a revised version of the agenda, the documents list and the participants list. \r\n\r\n\r\nYou are able to sort your documents by agenda number, document number, posted date, etc by clicking on the appropriate header of the publication table. Remember that for all the documents that have been posted today and before: *NO PRINTED COPIES* of SC documents will be provided by the Secretariat. \r\n\r\n\r\nPlease also note for Monday morning 18 November 2013:   \r\n•	Please pick up your FAO building passes early, the pass office opens at 8:30  \r\n•	The German Room (C269) will be open at 9:00 and the meeting will start at 10:00  \r\n•	We will be following the UN conference services seating plan and request SC members not to move their name plates   \r\n•	Coffee and pastries will be served at 9:30 in front of the meeting room as usual  \r\n•	Those who will receive DSA will have to collect them Casher Office (Building D, room D202, close to the Marble Stairs, open from 9:00 to 11:00 From Monday to Friday but if you go on Monday you would need to go before 10:00) and will need an ID card/passport to show their identity  \r\n•	We will have the cocktail on Monday evening (18:30) on the 7th floor of the B building (Marble Stairs, same place as in May). As for the last SC meeting, you are welcome to bring snacks from your country to have international diversity.  \r\n•	We will have the dinner on Wednesday evening at 19:30. The price will be 35 euros. For those who wish to come, we would be grateful if you could bring the money on Monday 18 Nov and if you could tell Tanja Lahti (tanja.lahti@fao.org) **by Friday 15 Nov** which menu you would like to choose (see enclosed document).  \r\n\r\nThank you very much\r\n\r\n\r\n**23 October**\r\n\r\nPosted: \r\n\r\n - 27_SC_2013_Nov: Recommendations Call for topics  \r\n\r\n - 30_SC_2013_Nov: Preparation for the SC’s discussion on the grain specification\r\n\r\n - 31_SC_2013_Nov: Steward’s summary of comments from SCCP - Appendix 1 to ISPM 12 (2006-003)\r\n\r\n - 32_SC_2013_Nov: Steward’s summary of comments from SCCP – Annex to ISPM 26 (2009-007)\r\n\r\n - 33_SC_2013_Nov: Compiled comments (including Steward’s response) - 2009-007: Draft ISPM - Establishment of fruit fly quarantine areas within a pest free area \r\n\r\n - 34_SC_2013_Nov: Compiled comments (including Steward’s response)- 2006-003: Draft Appendix 1 to ISPM 12:2011 - Electronic phytosanitary certificates, information on standard XML schemas, and exchange mechanisms\r\n\r\n - 35_SC_2013_Nov: Compiled comments (including Steward’s response)- 2006-031: Draft ISPM - Determination of host status of fruit to fruit flies (Tephritidae)\r\n\r\n - 36_SC_2013_Nov: Steward’s summary of comments from SCCP - Determination of host status of fruit to fruit flies(2006-031)\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso posted:\r\n\r\n - 2006-003: Appendix to ISPM 12 on Electronic certification, information on standard XML schemes and exchange mechanisms (2006-003)\r\n\r\n - 2006-031: Determination of host status of fruits and vegetables to fruit fly (Tephritidae) infestation (2006-031)\r\n\r\n - 2009-007: Establishment of fruit fly quarantine areas within a pest free area (for inclusion as Annex 1 of ISPM 26) (2009-007)\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso, updated versions of the Provisional Agenda (01_SC_2013_Nov), Documents List (02_SC_2013_Nov)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**21 October**\r\n\r\nPosted: \r\n\r\n- 22_SC_2013_Nov: Review of the IPPC Standard Setting Calendar\r\n\r\n- 23_SC_2013_Nov: Initiation of the review of the new Standard Setting procedure\r\n\r\n- 24_SC_2013_Nov: Update from the IPPC Secretariat – Standard Setting\r\n\r\n- 25_SC_2013_Nov: Framework for Standards Task Force\r\n\r\n- 26_SC_2013_Nov: Technical Support Document for Glossary Definition of Effective Dose\r\n\r\n- 28_SC_2013_Nov: Exchange of views on some comments from the member consultation in preparation for the 2014 May SC  \r\n\r\n- 29_SC_2013_Nov: IPPC ePhyto update\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso, updated versions of the Provisional Agenda (01_SC_2013_Nov), Documents List (02_SC_2013_Nov) and Participants List (03_SC_2013_Nov).\r\n\r\n\r\n**14 October**\r\n\r\nPosted:\r\n\r\n- 03_SC_2013_Nov: Participants List (provisional)\r\n\r\n\r\n**10 October**\r\n\r\nThe following documents were posted:\r\n\r\n- 15_SC_2013_Nov: SC Manual and mentoring\r\n\r\n- 16_SC_2013_Nov: Biodiversity and environmental considerations for expert drafting groups\r\n\r\n- 17_SC_2013_Nov: USA paper - Comments on strategic issues related to the draft specification for the development of a standard with a reduced scope on the international movement of grain\r\n\r\n- 18_SC_2013_Nov:Comments from ePhyto Steering Group on the draft appendix to ISPM 12 on Electronic certification\r\n\r\n- 19_SC_2013_Nov: Consistency across ISPMs\r\n\r\n- 20_SC_2013_Nov: Consistency in languages\r\n\r\n- 21_SC_2013_Nov: USA paper - Transparency in selecting TP and EWG experts\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso, updated versions of the Provisional Agenda (01_SC_2013_Nov) and Documents List (02_SC_2013_Nov).\r\n\r\n\r\n**30 September**\r\n\r\n- Updated Provisional Agenda posted\r\n\r\n- Provisional Documents List\r\n\r\n- Other SC 2013 November documents have also been posted today (01_SC_2013_Nov to 14_SC_2013_Nov, regardless the Participants List 03_SC_2013_Nov)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**11 September**\r\n\r\nThe 2013 November SC meeting will be held on 18-22 November 2013 at FAO Headquarters in Rome, Italy (German Room - C-269).\r\n\r\nPlease note that **04 October** is the deadline for registering to the meeting, submitting requests for funding and submitting any discussion paper to the Secretariat.\r\n\r\nWe have just posted below a **first version of the provisional agenda.** \r\n\r\nDraft ISPMs and draft Specifications: They are posted on the [IPPC Online Comment System (OCS)](http://ocs.ippc.int/). \r\n\r\nAs long as we receive the revised versions after the commenting period we will post them here. \r\n\r\n\r\nOther meeting documents will be posted in the next weeks. We intend to have all documents posted by 31 October.\r\n\r\n\r\nSo please check the SC restricted work area as we post new documents.\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you. Looking forward to see you all in November.\r\n\r\nRegards, \r\n\r\nIPPC Secretariat.','14579'),(599,'<p/>','14693'),(600,'<p/>','9054'),(601,'SC extraordinary working group 12-16 July 2004','9015'),(602,'Standards Committee Working Group 8-12 November 2004','9020'),(603,'Standards Committee 15-19 November 2004','9021'),(604,'<p/>','9055'),(605,'Standards Committee 25-29 April 2005','9028'),(606,'**Standards Committee 7-11 November 2005**','9036'),(607,'<p/>','9059'),(608,'**Standards Committee 8-12 May 2006**','9038'),(609,'**SC and SC-7 documents 6 - 17 November 2006**\r\n\r\n<b>Updated: 10 November 2006 (afternoon)</b><br>Draft ISPMs and reactions to comments by the SC-7 have been posted for the draft ISPMs on <li> recognition of PFAs and ALPPs <li> debarked and bark-free wood<li> establishment of ALPPs for fruit flies.<br><br><b><u>Meeting with the evaluation team</u></b>: the team conducting the evaluation of the IPPC has requested a meeting with all SC members. This meeting has been scheduled on <b>Tuesday 14 November at 17.30.</b><p><b>Updated: 8 November 2006 (evening)</b><br>Draft ISPMs and reactions to comments by the SC-7 have been posted for the following: <li>Amendments to the Glossary (SC document: 29)\r\n<li>Revision of ISPM No. 2 (SC document: 30)\r\n<li>Phytosanitary treatments for regulated pests (SC document: 31 - Posted with track changes turned off for better viewing). <p>The rest of the draft ISPMs will be posted here immediately after the SC-7 have finished their review. <p>The files are labelled &quot;For SC from SC-7&quot; and the corresponding SC agenda number is indicated. Those documents posted without agenda numbers are earlier versions. The SC is requested to focus on the SC-7 revisions of the draft ISPMs in their discussion at the upcoming meeting and to bring printed copies of the documents. <p>\r\nA reference binder containing all the country comments, along with responses to the comments, will be provided at the SC meeting. It is not necessary for each SC member to bring printed versions of the country comment tables.<p>\r\n\r\n<b>Anticipated deadlines</b><br> \r\n<li><b>October 16:</b> Compiled comments sent to stewards for review \r\n<li><b>October 20:</b> Compiled comments posted on the IPP\r\n<li><b>October 26:</b> Steward&quot;s reactions to comments and revised standards posted on IPP \r\n<li><b>November 6 - 10:</b> SC-7 reactions to comments and revised standards posted on IPP as they become available. </li><p>\r\nClick on the link <b>Expand text</b> below to see the SC-7 and SC tentative schedules.','9052'),(610,'<p/>','9078'),(611,'**Standards Committee 30 April - 4 May 2007**\r\n\r\n<b>SC meeting arrangements (30 April - 4 May 2007)</b> \r\n<br>Monday start: 9:00, Philippines room, C-277\r\n<p>The meeting will be conducted in English with interpretation into Arabic, Chinese, and Spanish.<p> We will adhere to the following schedule each day:\r\n<li><u>Morning:</u> Session: 09:00 to 10:15; Break: 10:15 to 10:45; Session: 10:45 to 12:30 \r\n<li><u>Lunch:</u> 12:30 to 14:00</u> \r\n<li><u>Afternoon:</u> Session: 14:00 to 15:15; Break: 15:15 to 15:45; Session: 15:45 to 17:30. \r\n<p>We will attempt to consider the agenda items in the following order, which is based on priority, amount of time the topic has been under development and prioritization of topics that will enable TPs and EWGs to continue working: \r\n<li><u>Monday:</u> Agenda items: 1-6 and 13\r\n<li><u>Tuesday:</u> Agenda items: 9.3, 10.1, 9.1, 8 and 12 (high priority items for continued work)\r\n<li><u>Wednesday and Thursday:</u> Agenda items: 7.1, 7.9, 7.8, 7.5, 7.7, 7.4, 7.2, 7.3 and 7.6\r\n<li><u>Friday morning:</u> Agenda items: 9.2, 9.4, 10.2, 11 and 14\r\n<li><u>Friday afternoon:</u> Agenda items: 15, 16 and 17.<p>\r\n<b>24 April 2007</b>\r\n<br>Today 24 April 2007-(17:30 Rome time) we have posted the last documents that we will be posting prior to the upcoming SC meeting (Sorry we are one day late). \r\n<br>The Pre-clearance papers and the CPM-2 Report appendices will be distributed at the meeting.<p>\r\n\r\n<b>18 April 2007</b>\r\n<br>The draft ISPM Establishment of areas of low pest prevalence for fruit flies and the comments submitted to CPM-2 and the steward (with responses) are now posted (docs: 27 and 28).<p>\r\n<b>17 April 2007</b>\r\n<br>The doucments list (doc: 2) and documents 14-26 are now posted. Please check this page often as documents will be added as they become available. The documents list will be updated continually indicating the new documents posted, and the publication date given below also corresponds to the date the document was posted.<p>\r\n<b>4 April 2007</b>\r\n<br>The CPM-2 has made some important decisions that will affect the work of the SC, in particular the draft ISPM for Establishment of ALPP for FF has been sent back for further work by the Steward and will be posted on <b>18 April 2007</b>, and the draft for Debarked and bark free wood has also been sent back to the SC for further consideration.<p>\r\nWe have set <b>23 April 2007</b> as the cut off date for posting documents on the SC work area and any other documents will be distributed at the meeting. Please print off all documents prior to the meeting as no hard copies will be available. Those SC members who do not have easy access to the documents due to technical limitations may request hard copies to be made for them no later than <b>23 April 2007</b>.','9058'),(612,'<b>18 October 2007</b><br>\r\nThe agenda and some documents for the forthcoming meeting are now available. Other documents will be posted progressively, and we therefore invite you to check the work area regularly.<p>\r\n<b>Special note for document 2007-SC-Nov-06-ADD below</b>: the zip file contains the 36 submissions of new topics received from countries. A binder containing these submissions will be available in the meeting room.\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><i>Tentative schedule leading up to the SC meeting:</i> \r\n<li>Monday, 22 October - Stewards&quot; responses to member comments and re-drafted ISPMs posted\r\n<li>29 October to 2 November – SC-7 meets and redrafts ISPMs (posted as they become available).\r\n\r\n<p><i>Tentative order for reviewing draft ISPMs at both the SC-7 and SC meetings</i>: \r\n<br>1. Amendments to the Glossary - Steward: John Hedley \r\n<br>2. Establishment of areas of low pest prevalence for fruit flies - Steward: Magda Gonzalez \r\n<br>3. Sampling of consignments - Steward: David Porritt \r\n<br>4. Developing a strategy to reduce or replace the use of methyl bromide for phytosanitary purposes - Steward: Mohammad Katbeh Bader \r\n<br>5. Debarked and bark-free wood - Steward: Ringolds Arnitis \r\n<br>6. Classification of commodities into phytosanitary risk categories - Steward: Diego Quiroga \r\n<br>7. Diagnostic protocol on Thrips palmi - Steward: Jens Unger.\r\n\r\n<p>SC sessions will be from 9:00 – 12:00 and 13:30 – 16:30 without breaks as the interpreters union no longer allows breaks in the 3-hour interpretation session. \r\n\r\n<p>In addition, the SPTA, which met from 1-5 October, has decided to only convene a meeting of the SC-7 in May 2008. As a result, <b>all decisions that need to be taken by the SC over the next year will have to be taken at the November 2007 meeting or by delegating the authority to the SC-7</b>. Stewards are requested to plan accordingly.','9070'),(613,'<p/>','9079'),(614,'**Standards Committee Working Group 5-9 May 2008**\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n28 April 2008\r\n\r\nIn accordance with the CPM-3 decision, some SC documents are available to contracting parties (contact points and IPP editors) and regional plant protection organizations. The documents list (2008-SC-May-02) indicates which documents are available. Documents that are not available are marked with \"restricted access\" by the title and the file is not visible.','9080'),(615,'**SC-7 and SC meetings 3-7 November and 10-14 November 2008 Salvador, Brazil** \r\n\r\n\r\n<b>  3 November 2008 </b>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nThe SC-7 began their meeting and the issue of the revision to ISPM No. 15 was discussed. The SC-7 were informed that the steward had submitted a revision to the draft ISPM well ahead of schedule. The SC-7 felt that this draft ISPM was extremely important and decided to add it to their agenda (shown below) and if possible the draft ISPM No. 15 will be added to the agenda of the SC.<p>\r\n<b>SC-7 Agenda</b> <br>\r\n1.Selection of Chair <br>\r\n2.Glossary of phytosanitary terms (Amendments to ISPM No. 5)<br> \r\n3.Categorization of commodities according to their phytosanitary risk <br> \r\n4.Terminology of the Convention on Biological Diversity (CBD) in relation to the Glossary of phytosanitary terms (proposed supplement to ISPM No. 5)<br> \r\n5. Revision to ISPM No. 15 <br> \r\n6.Structure and operation of post-entry quarantine facilities <br>\r\n<p>As usual, once the SC-7 completes a revision, these documents will be posted on the IPP in the SC restricted work area (<u>https://www.ippc.int/id/205586?language=en</u>).\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>  30 October 2008 </b>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Compiled member comments on  draft ISPMs</b><br> \r\nCompiled member comments on  draft ISPMs will be posted publicly on the IPP (<u>https://www.ippc.int/id/207742?language=en</u>) as the compilations are completed.\r\n<br>\r\n<p><b>CVs for experts nominated for TPs and EWGs</b><br>\r\nCVs for experts nominated for TPs and EWGs have now been posted in zip files on the IPP (<u>https://www.ippc.int/id/207854?language=en</u>). Summaries will be prepared and posted as they are completed. New TP members and experts for working groups will be selected from these CVs under agenda items 10.4 and 10.5.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<b>28 October 2008</b>\r\n<p>Comments with steward&quot;s responses and redrafted ISPMs for categorization of commodities, post-entry quarantine facilities, CBD terminology and glossary amendments are now posted for the SC-7. These documents have not been given numbers but are all titled &quot;To SC-7: ...&quot;\r\n\r\n<p><b>23 October 2008</b>\r\n<br>Compiled comments have now been posted at the following link: <u>https://www.ippc.int/id/207742?language=en</u>\r\n\r\n<p><b>7 October 2008</b>\r\n<br>Dear SC members, Stewards and confirmed observers,\r\n<p>Please note the following dates in regards to the preparation of meeting documents:\r\n<p>\r\n<li><b>30 September 2008</b> Member comment period closed. The Secretariat is now compiling comments.\r\n\r\n<li><b>8 October 2008</b> Compiled comments on definitions will be sent to the TPG. The steward and TPG will have 14 days (including weekends) to respond to comments, adjust the draft terms (with tracked changes) and return them to the Secretariat.\r\n\r\n<li><b>10 October 2008</b> SC, SC-7, stewards and observers must confirm their participation directly to Ms. Isabella Liberto (Isabella.Liberto@fao.org)\r\n\r\n<li><b>10 October 2008</b> Compiled comments will be posted on the IPP (public) and sent to stewards (only comments on those draft ISPMs that will be considered at the November 2008 meetings will be compiled). Stewards will have 12 days (including weekends) to respond to comments, adjust the draft ISPM (with tracked changes) and return it to the Secretariat.\r\n\r\n<li><b>10 October 2008</b> SC members requesting travel assistance must submit their request directly to Ms. Isabella Liberto (Isabella.Liberto@fao.org)\r\n\r\n<li><b>22 October 2008</b> Stewards submit to Secretariat their responses to comments and a tracked changes version of the draft ISPM.\r\n\r\n<li><b>24 October 2008</b> Secretariat posts steward&quot;s responses to comments and redrafted ISPM in the restricted work area for SC members. SC-7 to study in preparation for their meeting.\r\n\r\n<li><b>24 October 2008</b> Discussion papers due, please submit to the IPPC Secretariat and we will post them as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n<li><b>3-7 November 2008</b> SC-7 meets, SC-7 redrafted ISPMs and responses to comments will be posted as they become available. \r\n\r\n<li><b>10-14 November 2008</b> SC meets \r\n\r\n<p><u>NOTE:</u> Some draft ISPMs will be considered under the extended time schedule and due dates for these drafts will be agreed to at the SC meeting.','9088'),(616,'<p/>','9097'),(617,'**Standards Committee 4-8 May 2009**\r\n\r\nThe formal deadline for posting documents for the May 2009 SC meeting has been extended until COB (Rome, Italy) Friday, 24 April. Any documents received after this deadline will not be posted on the IPP and will be distributed at the SC meeting. Complete sets of documents for the meeting can be downloaded after COB 24 April.','9098'),(618,'**Standards Committee Working Group 11-13 May 2009**\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Standards Committee Working Group (SC-7) will meet 11-13 May 2009 to review member comments submitted during the 2008 member consultation period, and the drafts that have been modified by stewards in response to member comments. These revised drafts will be forwarded to the Standards Committee in November 2009.','9099'),(619,'**Standards Committee 9-13 November 2009 Rome, Italy (FAO, German Room)**','9100'),(620,'<p/>','9117'),(621,'<p/>','9113'),(622,'Standards Committee, 26-30 April 2010 Rome, Italy German room, C-269 (Start time: 10:00)\r\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nThe deadline for posting documents for the April 2010 SC Meeting was March 19, 2010.\r\n\r\nAs of April 8th, all papers except the update on the standard setting workprogramme, agenda item 12, had been posted. This paper will be posted at a later time.\r\n\r\nWorking papers under Agenda item 13 that have been carried over from previous meetings and that have not been modified retain their original document numbers, ie, 2009-SC-May-XX. However, their agenda numbers correspond to the April 2010 meeting agenda. \r\n\r\nPlease note that in order to sort documents by agenda number, date, etc it is necessary to press the \"all\" button.','9114'),(623,'Working Group of the Standards Committee (SC-7)\r\n-----------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nMeetings of the Commission on Phytosanitary Measures\r\nWorking Group of the Standards Committee (SC-7)\r\n03 – 06 May, 2010\r\nRome, Italy\r\n\r\n    This meeting will convene at FAO headquarters in Rome, Italy from  03 - 06 May (SC-7) 2010 in the Canada Room (A-356).   Please note that the SC-7 meeting is a four day meeting. You are requested to make travel arrangements to arrive before the SC meeting begins (10:00 Monday morning) and depart after the SC-7 meeting ends (17:00 Thursday  afternoon). All members are requested to confirm their participation directly to Ms. Tanja Lahti (tanja.lahti@fao.org) no later than 6 April 2010 in order to finalize local arrangements.','9115'),(624,'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">Updates for the upcoming November 2010 SC meeting - Brent Larson, Standards Officer</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">Proposed schedule:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Mon</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Holiday in Italy, FAO catering services closed for Monday consider bringing lunch and snacks.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">AM: Agenda items 1 &amp; 2</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">PM: Agenda item 3.1 ( ISPM 7)</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Tues </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">AM:&amp; PM Agenda item 3.2 ( ISPM12) </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">18:00 Cocktail</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Wed</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">AM: Agenda item 3.3 (draft ISPM on Fruit fly trapping- </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Steward: Walther Enkerlin</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">) and Agenda item </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">3.4 (C</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">onsistency in ISPM 5).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">PM: Specs for approval: Agenda items </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">4.1 (Draft Spec: Air containers), 4.5 (Draft Spec: Waste disposal) then 4.2 (Inspection procedures) and 4.3 / 4.4</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Specs for approval for MC: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Agenda items 4.6 (Draft Spec: Outbreak FF Free areas), 4.9 (Draft Spec: seed) and then in order of agenda 4.7 / 4.8 / 4.10 / 4.11 and 4.12</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">20:00 Group Dinner</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Thur</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">AM: Agenda items <span>&nbsp;</span>3.5 (Revision of ANNEX 1to ISPM 15-</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Steward: Thomas Schroder</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">), <span>&nbsp;</span>2.4.3 (Selection of nominations) and then continue work on other draft Specifications 4.4 / 4.3 / 4.13 / 4.14</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">PM: Contingency planning and follow up of previous outstanding agenda points.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Fri</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">AM: Agenda 5, 6 &amp; 7</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">PM- Adopt report, close<br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;_______________________________________________________________________</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">28 October 2010</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"EN\">See proposed schedule above. Reminder that Monday 1 November is an Italian holiday and some things maybe closed. You may wish to bring your own snacks as the FAO catering facilities will be closed on Monday. Have a safe flight.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">26 October 2010</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">We have now posted all of the SC documents for the November SC meeting except for the extractions from the reports of the Bureau and SPTA meetings (docs 47 and 48) which will be posted on the 27 October 2010.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">We have closed the documents list and&nbsp;will not post&nbsp;any more documents or revisions after the 27 October 2010, the last document number will be&nbsp;2010_SC_Nov_50.&nbsp; Any additional documents will be posted on the first day of the SC meeting and hard copies will be made available to all participants.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">We have&nbsp;updated and reposted the Agenda (Doc 01), documents list (doc 02) and the participants list (Doc 03).&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">On Wednesday&nbsp; 27 October we will be posting a tentative schedule for the order&nbsp;of&nbsp;discussion of agenda items. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">22 October 2010</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">I had hoped to have all the documents for the SC November meeting posted today but we are still waiting for a few more documents and I also need to review them before posting.&nbsp; <strong>We are extending the deadline in hopes to have all the documents posted by close of day next Tuesday 26 November 2010</strong>.&nbsp; After this date we will not post any more SC documents until the week of the SC meeting, for these documents we will provide you a hard copy. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;I would like to bring to your attention the urgent financial crisis of the IPPC Secretariat and the proposed massive cuts to the standard setting programme (see IPP for letter in languages: <a href=\"index.php?id=1110664&amp;tx_news_pi1%5bshowUid%5d=1106159\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=1110664&amp;tx_news_pi1[showUid]=1106159</span></a> ).&nbsp; Please give it some thought as we many need to be flexible and consider innovative methods of operating the SC if we wish to keep standard setting alive in 2011 if there are no responses to the call for resources.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">20 October 2010</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">We had attempted to provide you with a hypertext linked agenda but have discoverd this is not technically possible.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">08 October 2010</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">Please note that the SC meeting has been moved to the German room instead of the Mexico room.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">13 September 2010</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">The agenda and the documents list will be updated weekly (see date posted on both the IPP and on the downloaded document), so please ensure you have downloaded the latest version.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">19 August 2010</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">Letters of invite have now gone out to all SC members and RPPOs. I hope to have a draft agenda out within the next few weeks.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">Stewards are reminded to submit their draft Specifications.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">You may wish to note that we have two new SC members </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN-GB\">Mr. Udorn UNAHAWUTTI (Thailand) and Mr. Basim MUSTAFA KHALIL (Iraq)</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">16 July 2010</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt; line-height: normal; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \" lang=\"EN\">SC7 Revisions to the ISPM 7 &amp; 12 are posted for SC review.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','9116'),(625,'<p/>','27498'),(626,'**28 April 2014**\r\n\r\nWe have posted today under the SC restricted area two new papers (along with a revised agenda and document list):\r\n- 2006-031: proposal from the steward on the fruit fly host status draft standard, following the formal objections prior CPM (agenda item 9.1)\r\n- 33_SC_2014_May: summary of SC e-decisions (agenda item 7.3).\r\nWe do not intend to post new documents this week. These four documents will be printed and distributed to SC members on Monday morning, together with the revisions of documents 11 and 32 (see below). Thanks\r\n\r\n**23 April 2014** A revised version of document 11 (TPG comments on the draft ISPM on Seed) was posted today. Modifications were done to paragraph numbers.\r\n\r\n**22 April 2014** A revised version of document 32 was posted today. Modifications were done to paragraph 208 and to the formatting.\r\n\r\nThe 2014 February TPG report is now posted and a direct link to it has been posted below.\r\n\r\n**17 April 2014**\r\n\r\nWe posted today remaining documents for the 5-9 May 2014 Standards Committee (SC) meeting (including revised versions of the agenda, the documents list and the participants list).\r\n\r\nHowever there are still a few papers that will be posted later:\r\n\r\n- Summary on polls and forums discussed on e-decision site (SC agenda item 7.3), since we have a SC poll closing today and a SC forum still on-going;\r\n- A new version of the draft Determination of host status of fruit to fruit flies (Tephritidae) (2006-031), on which the Steward is currently working (after the formal objection that was submitted prior CPM-9) (SC agenda item 9.1)\r\n- Possibly a document from the TPPT regarding the formal objections received on cold treatments prior CPM9 (SC agenda item 9.1).\r\n- Possible paper for the General update from the IPPC Secretariat (SC agenda item 9.2)\r\n\r\nAlso please note the 2014 February TPG report is not posted yet but will be posted early next week.\r\n\r\nWe would like to encourage you to already start thinking before the SC meeting about the assignment of new stewards or assistant stewards (see document 16_SC_2014_May_Rev1, agenda item 5.2). According the nomination process, a new steward / assistant steward would need to be nominated by a SC member from another region, seconded by another SC member from a third region.\r\n\r\nPlease also note for Monday morning 5 May 2014:\r\n\r\n* Please pick up your FAO building passes early, the pass office opens at 8:30\r\n* The German Room (C269) will be open at 9:00 and the meeting will start at 10:00\r\n* We will be following the UN conference services seating plan and request SC members not to move their name plates\r\n* Coffee and pastries will be served at 9:30 in front of the meeting room as usual\r\n* Those who will receive DSA will have to collect them Casher Office (Building D, room D202, close to the Marble Stairs, open from 9:00 to 11:00 From Monday to Friday but if you go on Monday you would need to go before 10:00) and will need an ID card/passport to show their identity\r\n* We will have the cocktail on Monday evening (18:30) on the 7th floor of the B building (Marble Stairs, same place as in November). As for the last SC meeting, we would be very grateful if you could bring snacks from your country so that we have international diversity. It would be nice also if you can add a small label with the name of the country on the food package.\r\n* We will have the dinner as usual on Wednesday evening at 19:30. We will provide more information later.\r\n\r\nAlso note that 18 and 21 April, and 1 and 2 May are bank holidays in FAO.\r\n\r\nThank you\r\n\r\n**14 April 2014**\r\n\r\nWe have posted a revised version of the Provisional agenda, the Documents list and working paper 16 Rev. 1 together with\r\n\r\nWorking papers 18 and 19\r\n\r\n**11 April 2014**\r\n\r\nWe have posted a revised version of the Provisional agenda and the Documents list together with:\r\n\r\nWorking papers 10 to 17\r\n\r\n**28 March 2014**\r\n\r\nWe have posted a revised version of the Provisional agenda and the Documents list together with:\r\n\r\nWorking paper 10_SC_2014_May\r\n\r\n**27 March 2014**\r\n\r\nWe have posted a revised version of the Provisional agenda and the Documents list together with:\r\n\r\nParticipants list\r\nDraft specification on Revision of ISPM 6:1997 (Guidelines for surveillance)\r\nWorking papers 07 to 09\r\n\r\n**12 March 2014**\r\n\r\nWe have posted a revised version of the Provisional agenda together with:\r\n\r\n- Draft specification on International movement of grain \r\n- Working paper 06_SC_2014_May\r\n\r\n**3 March 2014**\r\n\r\nWe have posted a revised version of the provisional agenda together with:\r\n\r\nDocuments list\r\nDraft ISPM on Used equipments\r\nDraft specification on Import permits\r\nMore links to meeting reports which are now available.\r\n\r\n**25 February 2014**\r\n\r\nThe 2014 May SC meeting will be held on 5-9 May 2014 at FAO Headquarters in Rome, Italy.\r\n\r\nPlease note that 14 March is the deadline for registering to the meeting, submitting requests for funding and submitting any discussion paper to the Secretariat.\r\n\r\nWe have just posted below a first version of the provisional agenda together with:\r\n\r\n- 3 draft ISPMs: International movement of seed, sea containers (version submitted to the 2013 member consultation) and phytosanitary pre-clearance (same version already submitted to the 2013 May SC meeting)\r\n- 2 working papers (04_SC_2014_May and 05_SC_2014_May)\r\n- Several links to meeting reports and other documents\r\n- The SC invitation letter and the local information document\r\n\r\nThe draft ISPM on Used equipment, which is also on the agenda, will be posted by the end of the week, along with other possible papers. The draft Amendments to ISPM 5 and other meeting documents will be posted in the next weeks as soon as possible. We intend to have all documents posted by 17 April.\r\n\r\nSo please check the SC restricted work area as we post new documents.\r\n\r\nThanks for your cooperation. Looking forward to seeing you in May.\r\n\r\nThe IPPC Secretariat','27497'),(627,'**30 July 2014**\r\n\r\nDear SC members and participants,\r\n\r\nThe 2014 November SC meeting will be convened in FAO headquarters, Rome, Italy from 10-14 November 2014.\r\n\r\nPlease note that the deadline for registering to the meeting (by simple email to the Secretariat)and submitting requests for funding is **26 September.**\r\n\r\nThe deadline for submitting any discussion paper to the Secretariat is **03 October.**\r\n\r\nThe deadline for stewards (from SCCP) to send the response to the comments and revised draft ISPMs is **17 October 2014.**\r\n\r\nWe have posted below the draft ISPMs that are out for the SCCP (same version as in OCS). Once the stewards revise the drafts after the SCCP, the versions will be updated. The drafts are:\r\n\r\n- 1994-001: Draft Amendments to ISPM 5 (Glossary of phytosanitary terms)\r\n\r\n- 2005-004: International movement of growing media in association with plants for planting\r\n\r\n- 2005-010: Phytosanitary procedures for Fruit Fly (Tephritidae) management\r\n\r\n2006-029: International movement of wood\r\n\r\nThe invitation letter will be send out soon. The provisional agenda will be posted a.s.a.p. So please check the SC restricted work area as we post new documents.\r\n\r\nThanks for your cooperation. Looking forward to see you in November.\r\n\r\nThe IPPC Secretariat.','27499'),(628,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\n**SC-7 2014**  \r\n*Photo posted on 29 May 2014*\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**25 February 2014**\r\n\r\nThe 2014 SC-7 meeting will be convened in FAO headquarters, Rome, Italy from  12 to 16 May 2014. \r\n\r\n\r\nYou are requested to confirm your participation by simple email directly to Ms Tanja Lahti <Tanja.Lahti@fao.org> no later than **14 March 2014** in order to finalize local arrangements (this deadline is also for submitting requests for funding).\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease note that **14 March** is also the deadline for submitting the SC-7 documents to the Secretariat. \r\n\r\nThe draft ISPMs on Phytosanitary procedures for fruit fly (Tephritidae) management (2005-010) and Amendments to ISPM 5: Glossary of Phytosanitary Terms (1994-001) and related documents will be posted as soon as possible. \r\n\r\nWe intend to have all documents posted by 17 April.\r\n\r\nIf you have problems accessing the restricted area or downloading the documents, please contact Ms Paola Sentinelli <Paola.Sentinelli@fao.org>.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks for your cooperation. Looking forward to seeing you in May.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe IPPC Secretariat\r\n\r\n_______\r\n\r\n**Updates:**\r\n\r\n- 2014-04-07: Participants List posted (all meeting documents posted).\r\n\r\n\r\n- 2014-03-28: All meeting documents, except the participants list, were posted. \r\n              Updated agenda and Documents List posted today.\r\n\r\n- 2014-03-24: Draft 1994-001 and TPG responses to the 2013 member comments (document 13_SC7_2014_May) posted. \r\n              Updated Agenda and Documents List posted. \r\n\r\n- 2014-03-18: Documents from agenda item 01 to 4.3 are posted (except Participants List). \r\n\r\n- 2014-03-18: Updated (Revised versions) of the draft ISPMs were posted (Draft ISPMs: 2005-004, 2006-029 and 2005-010).\r\n              \r\n- 2014-03-12: Updated version of Compiled comments with TPG considerations for draft ISPM on Movement of growing media, updated Agenda and Documents list posted.\r\n\r\n- 2014-03-03: Updated version of Compiled comments with Steward\'s responses for draft ISPM on Movement of growing media posted.\r\n\r\n- 2014-02-26: Draft ISPMs posted: Movement of growing media in association with plants for planting in international trade (2005-004) and Management of phytosanitary risks in the international movement of wood (2006-029).\r\n\r\n- 2014-02-26: Documents posted: 01_SC7_2014_May (Draft agenda), 02_SC7_2014_May (Draft documents list), 04_SC7_2014_May and 05_SC7_2014_May\r\n\r\n- 2014-02-27: Updated version of the document list and draft agenda posted. Posted also draft ISPM on Phytosanitary Procedures for Fruit Fly (Tephritidae) Management (2005-10) and 06_SC7_2014_May\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/img_1963_toipp.jpg','27500'),(629,'<p/>','9200'),(630,'**2011 Focus Group for Improving the IPPC Standard Setting Process**\r\n\r\n\r\nThe IPPC Secretariat welcomes you to the restricted acecss area for participants to the meeting on the 2011 Focus Group on improving the IPPC standard setting process. The Meeting will take place 25-29 July 2011 hosted by EPPO at their Headquarters in Paris, France.\r\n \r\nUpdates on activities will be posted below by date, please log on frequently to find out what is happening for the preparation for this meeting.\r\n \r\n2011-07-20\r\nFinal update before the meeting\r\nToday is the closing date for documents and we have finished posting additional documents. We will not post any more documents prior to the meeting.\r\n\r\nPlease make sure to log onto the IPP and download the revised documents (Agenda, Documents list and Participants list) and the more recently posted documents.\r\n\r\nWe note that there are still some summary papers pending (see Agenda). When you have competed these please send us an electronic copy and bring 15 hardcopies for distribution at the meeting.\r\n\r\nWe wish you all safe travels and look forward to seeing you on Monday morning at 10:00 am.\r\n\r\n2011-07-02\r\nTravel Arrangements update\r\n1. The deadline for requesting travel assistance from the Secretariat has passed and we assume all your travel arrangements have been made.\r\n \r\n2. Please confirm your participation directly to Ms Tanja Lahti (tanja.lahti@fao.org) immediately (if you haven’t already done so).\r\n \r\n3. Once you have arranged your flight and hotel, please send Ms Stephanie Dubon (stephanie.dubon@fao.org) your flight information and hotel name so we can ensure everyone arrives safely to the meeting.\r\n \r\n4. The meeting will convene at EPPO Offices in Paris, France from 25-29 July 2011. This is a five-day meeting: therefore, we request you make travel arrangements to arrive before the meeting begins (10:00 Monday morning) and depart after the meeting ends (17:00 Friday afternoon).\r\n \r\n5. If necessary, please make proper visa arrangements for travelling to France. The IPPC Secretariat would like to draw your attention to the strict provisions in force regarding entry into France, including the refusal of entry to persons not having the required visas. Participants requiring entry visas must obtain these from the French Consulate or Diplomatic Mission in their country before departing for France.\r\n2011-06-28\r\nThere are 21 discussion papers for review. Specific FG members are requested to review the following discussion papers and develop a brief discussion paper (by 15 July 2011) to summarize the important aspects of each document and highlight the relevant sections.\r\n\r\nDoc 07: MUSTAFA KHALIL\r\nDoc 08: GRANT / RYMER\r\nDoc 09: GRANT / RYMER\r\nDoc 10: GRANT / RYMER\r\nDoc 14: MUSTAFA KHALIL\r\nDoc 15: SAKALA\r\nDoc 16: PALACIN\r\nDoc 19: BECH\r\nDoc 20: FUKUSHIMA\r\nStandard setting organizations are requested to prepare a brief discussion paper explaining their standard setting processes: KAHN, PELLAUX\r\n\r\nMembers representing regions are encouraged to discuss with NPPOs and RPPOs in their regions to see if they have any suggestions to help improve the IPPC standard setting process.\r\n\r\nAn e-mail went out to all NPPOs, RPPOs, SC and Bureau members to inform them they can submit discussion paper through FG members.','9201'),(631,'<h3>Focus Group on the review of standard setting procedures16-20 July 2007, Rome, Italy</h3>\r\n\r\n<b>9 July 2007</b>\r\n<br>The documents list (document 2) has been updated with corresponding agenda numbers.<p>\r\n<b>6 July 2007</b>\r\n<br>Documents for the Focus Group meeting are now posted. Please endeavour to bring your own copies of the documents to the meeting. If you are unable to download them, please contact stacie.johnston@fao.org to request that a set be made for you. <p>\r\n<b>Excerpt from the Report of CPM-2: </b>\r\n<br>100. The CPM:</b><br>\r\n1.    Decided to convene a Focus Group to review the IPPC standard setting procedures, in particular areas discussed under CPM-2 agenda items 9.4, 9.5, 9.7 and 10.1.2, and invited members to submit comments to the Secretariat on these agenda items by 1 May 2007;\r\n<br>2.    Adopted the terms of reference for the Focus Group as presented in Appendix 8; [See document 04 below]\r\n<br>3.    Decided that the Focus Group would be composed of 10 persons (as selected by a Friends of the Chair meeting, with one person per FAO region and three other members) as presented in Appendix 8; [See document 03 below]\r\n<br>4.    Agreed that, at the meeting of the SPTA in October 2007, a two-day session be held to analyze the findings of the Focus Group, and the outcome be considered by the SC and CPM.\r\n<p>Focus Group members are reminded that in addition to submitting written comments on the above documents they may also develop discussion papers prior to the meeting for consideration and discussion at the Focus Group meeting.','9062'),(632,'Focus Group 2012','9265'),(633,'To access meeting documents and information for expert working groups (EWGs), click on the appropriate year for the EWG in the sidebar to the right.','9046'),(634,'Topic:  Minimizing pest movement by sea containers and conveyances in international trade.\r\n\r\nWelcome to the work area for the development of an International Standard for Phytosanitary Measures (ISPM) on Minimizing pest movement by sea containers and conveyances in international trade. As this will be an important standard, which will have a broad impact affecting stakeholders outside of the traditional Phytosanitary world, the approach used for the development of the standard will be comprehensive in nature. The EWG meeting is planned to be hosted by Malaysia in May 2012. A significant amount of development work will be carried out \"virtually\" prior to the meeting of the Expert Working Group (EWG). This work area and the associated forum are some of the tools that will be used.\r\n\r\nA Steering committee for this group was formed and it developed an initial draft of the ISPM which was then circulated to the EWG members for comment in 2011.  The Steering Committee met in November 2011 and reviewed all the comments received on this draft. The link to the documents from this meeting is to the right of this screen (2011-11 SCSC meeting). The draft ISPM that came from this meeting will be used as the starting point for the EWG meeting in May. It is available on the link to the right of this screen for the EWG meeting (2012 - 05 EWG meeting).\r\n\r\nA discussion forum has been created and is below. Please feel free to join in or to start a new thread if there are any issues you would like to discuss.\r\n\r\nA list of background documents is also below. Review of these is suggested prior to the EWG meeting.\r\n\r\n ','9170'),(635,'This is a forum to support discussion on Sea Containers.\r\n\r\nClick [here](/forums/seacontainers-forum) to see the **active forums**.\r\n\r\nClick [here](/node/15368) to see the **closed** and **archived** forums.\r\n','9198'),(636,'Documents for the upcoming meeting will be posted below as they are developed.\r\n\r\n**2011-11-03**\r\n\r\nA revised Agenda has been posted. All the documents are now available.\r\n\r\n**2011-10-13**\r\n\r\nThe draft participants list and the local information document have been posted.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n**2011-10-12**\r\n\r\nWe are finalizing the agenda and local information documents and hope to have them posted in the next day or so.','9224'),(637,'Please note that the meeting is taking place in Mutiara Room, Level 2 of the  Puteri Pacific Hotel.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nDocuments for the upcoming EWG meeting will be posted below as they become available. Please make sure to bring copies of all documents to the meeting, there will be no facilities to print them there.','9249'),(638,'<p/>','14663'),(639,'**2013-05-28**\r\n\r\nPlease note that documents 13 to 18 were posted on this page, while the Agenda and Documents List were updated.\r\n\r\n**2013-05-23**\r\n\r\nPlease note that documents 9 to 12 were posted on this page, while the Agenda, Documents List, and Participants List were updated.\r\n\r\n**2013-05-07**\r\n\r\nPlease note that Brazilian comments on the Specification 48 have been posted (EWGUsedEquip_2013_May_08), together with an updated agenda.\r\n\r\n**2013-04-30**\r\n\r\nDue date for submission of discussion papers, only 2 papers submitted, Adam (Australia) and Melaine (New Zealand), they are posted below.\r\n\r\nHotel does not have you all registered, please do so immediately or they may release the rooms.\r\n\r\nAlso once you have your flights booked please inform Tanja Lahti (Tanja.Lahti@fao.org).\r\n\r\n**2013-04-10**\r\n\r\nWe had posted a wrong version of the participants list (document no. 4), the correct version has now been posted.\r\n\r\n**2013-04-03**\r\n\r\nThis will be where we update you on the arrangments for this EWG and post meeting documents below. I will try to update this often to keep you informed.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBrent Larson, IPPC Secretariat','14665'),(640,'**14 June 2013**\r\n\r\nThe updated Agenda, Documents list and Participants list have been posted today. Document 27 was posted on 12 June\r\n\r\n**6 June 2013**\r\n\r\nMs Julie Aliaga, one of the assistant stewards and also a Standards Committee (SC) member, has been invited to the meeting and she is now planning to attend the meeting. \r\n\r\nSome of you have asked us whether it was possible to already give comments on the discussion papers already posted.\r\nIf you wish, you can send additional papers to us by Wednesday 12 June with your comments (or any other discussion paper you wish to send) and we will then post these so it is shared with all EWG participants. We do not intend to post any paper after the 14 June. All these documents should be downloaded before the meeting as we won’t provide printed copies.\r\n\r\nOtherwise you can of course prepare your comments for direct input during the EWG meeting.\r\n\r\n\r\n**31 May 2013**\r\n\r\nPlease note that Documents 25 and 26 have been posted today along with the updated Documents list and Agenda.\r\n\r\n**28 May 2013**\r\n\r\nPlease note that Document 24 (Discussion paper by Mr N.M. Nico Horn) has been posted today along with the updated Documents list and Agenda.\r\n\r\n**23 May 2013**\r\n\r\nPlease note that the following documents have been posted today:\r\n\r\n- Document 01 (Updated Agenda)\r\n- Document 02 (Documents List)\r\n- Document 08 (Discussion paper by Ms Grimault)\r\n- Document 09 (Discussion paper by Mr Hancocks)\r\n- Documents 10 - 22 (Discussion papers by ISF)\r\n- Document 23 (Discussion paper by Ms Levi)\r\n\r\n**16 May 2013**\r\n\r\nPlease note that Document 07 (Discussion paper by Mr Asomaning) has been posted today.\r\n\r\n**13 May 2013**\r\n\r\nPlease note that Document 06 (Discussion paper by NARGS) has been posted today.\r\n\r\nWe would like to remind you of the followind deadlines coming soon:\r\n\r\n-     For those who have not done it yet, we kindly remind you to confirm your **participation** to the meeting no later than **20 May**.\r\n-      Participants are kindly requested to use the reservation form (posted below) to confirm the hotel reservation at the given rate. This should be done by **15th May** (availability of rooms may not be guaranteed after that date).\r\n-   The deadline for submission of all **discussion papers** to the Secretariat is the **20 May 2013**. We really encourage you to prepare ahead of time and submit your ideas to the Secretariat so we can post documents in advance and share them with the other EWG members\r\n\r\n\r\nMany thanks for your cooperation\r\n\r\n**22 April 2013**\r\n\r\nThis page will be where we update you on the arrangments for this EWG and post meeting documents below. We will try to update it often to keep you informed.\r\n\r\nDocuments 01 (Agenda), 03 (participants list), 04 (local information) and 05 (specification) have been posted today. The invitation to the EWG will be sent shortly.\r\n\r\nCéline GERMAIN, IPPC Secretariat','14666'),(641,'<p/>','14664'),(642,'To access 2005 Expert Working Group (EWG) meeting documents, click on the appropriate EWG in the sidebar to the left.','9016'),(643,'Background: The revision of ISPM No. 2 (Guidelines for pest risk analysis) was put on the ICPM work programme in 2003. Expert working groups to revise the standard met in January and June 2004. In April 2005, the Standards Committee decided for another expert working group meeting to be held 31 October - 2 November 2005.\r\n\r\nOperation: The documents for the meeting are posted below. Any member wishing to submit a document should e-mail it to Brent Larson (brent.larson@fao.org). More details on the meeting are available at the following link:\r\nsee more...','9011'),(644,'<p/>','9012'),(645,'ISPM No. 14 (The use of integrated measures in a systems approach for pest risk management) provides the general guidelines related to the pest risk management options by the application of integrated measures in a systems approach with the objective of satisfying phytosanitary requirements. The Interim Commission on Phytosanitary Measures identified a need for a specific standard on the risk management of citrus canker (Xanthomonas axonopodis p.v. citri) for citrus fruit.\r\nWorking Group members: Steward: Mr Odilson Ribeiro e Silva (Brazil), odilson@agricultura.gov.br\r\nIPPC Contact: Mr David Nowell, Dave.Nowell@fao.org\r\nMs Francoise Poliakoff (France), francoise.poliakoff@agriculture.gouv.fr\r\nMr José Adalberto Zuniga Reyes (Honduras), zunigajose@hotmail.com\r\nMr Lawrence Brown (USA), lawrence.g.brown@aphis.usda.gov\r\nMs Maria Inés Ares (Uruguay), mares@mgap.gub.uy\r\nMr Olivier Pruvost (France – Réunion), olivier.pruvost@cirad.fr\r\nMs Ana Maria Peralta (COSAVE - hosts), lbbimgap@adinet.com.uy\r\nMr Pablo Cortese (Argentina - hosts),\r\npcortese@sinavimo.com.ar see more...','9013'),(646,'<p/>','9026'),(647,'<p/>','9027'),(648,'<p/>','10731'),(649,'<p/>','10732'),(650,'Documents and discussion papers for this meeting will be posted below. Documents will be posted by the Secretariat as they are received and the \"publication date\" will be displayed.\r\n\r\nDocuments previously distributed for this meeting will have the original date (2005-01-27) for the meeting added to the title.\r\n\r\nAs ICPM-7 has adopted the Standard on guidelines for Inspection, the \"ISPM-Draft-2004-Guidelines Inspection 2005-01-27\" posted on 2005/05/09 has been replaced by \"ISPM No 23: Guidelines for inspection-2005-04-07\".','9022'),(651,'Working Group members: Steward: Mr Abdellah Challoui (Morocco), challaoui@yahoo.fr\r\nIPPC Contact: Mr Hesham Abuelnaga, Hesham.Abuelnaga@fao.org\r\nMs María Fernanda WagnerZuniga Reyes (Argentina), fernandawagner@datafull.com, mwagner@senasa.gov.ar\r\nMr Solke Harmen De Boer (Canada ), deboers@inspection.gc.ca\r\nMr Arnaud Bontemps (France), Arnaud.bontemps@agriculture.gouv.fr\r\nMs Tamsin Elizabeth Smales (New Zealand), smalest@maf.govt.nz\r\nMr Walter P. Gould (USA), walter.p.gould@aphis.usda.gov\r\nUnable to attend: Mr Marcos Muñoz (Chile), marco.munoz@sag.gob.cl','9023'),(652,'<p/>','10733'),(653,'Internationally, there are large numbers of pests associated with potato propagative material. Since potato minitubers and micropropagation material are intended for use in vegetative propagation, the risk of spreading pests is increased. Certain micropropagation processes can free propagative material from pests and therefore can be used as the basis for importing healthy material. Consequently, the export certification of such material is important and its basis may be harmonized.\r\n\r\nWorking Group members: Steward: Mr. Obbineni Ramalinga Reddy (India), obbinenirr@rediffmail.com \r\nIPPC Contact: Mr. Hesham Abuelnaga, Hesham.abuelnaga@fao.org\r\nMr. Marcelo Atilio Huarte (Argentina), huarte@balcarce.inta.gov.ar\r\nMr. Cameron Duff Reyes (Canada), duffc@inspection.gc.ca\r\nMr. Ishwar Dass Garg (India), idgarg@cpri.hp.nic.in\r\nMr. Hendrik van de Haar (Netherlands), hhaar@nak.nl \r\nMr. Sergie Kopen Bang (Papua New Guinea), naridr@global.net.pg \r\nMr. Niphone Thaveechai (Thailand), agrnpt@ku.ac.th\r\nMr. Colin Jeffries (UK), colin.jeffries@sasa.gsi.gov.uk','9033'),(654,' **Scope and purpose**\r\n\r\nDuring ICPM-7 it was agreed that general guidance for the recognition of pest free areas (PFAs) and areas of low pest prevalence (ALPPs) (referred to as regionalization) should be developed.\r\n\r\nThe standard will outline the main criteria for the recognition of PFAs and ALPPs. Furthermore it will provide guidance on the process that may need to be followed by both the importing and exporting countries for recognition of such areas. This is to ensure that importing and exporting countries have appropriate guidance on the activities required under the IPPC and its standards, that exporting countries can achieve recognition of regionalization without undue delay while importing countries can continue to maintain their appropriate level of protection.\r\n\r\nThis standard will not include specified timelines for the steps outlined within the general guidance.\r\n\r\nThe ICPM, at its seventh session in 2005, tasked the Focus Group (FG) with developing the Terms of Reference and composition of a working group to carry out a feasibility study on the international recognition of pest free areas (PFAs). Although this is not the task of this Expert Working Group, the Focus group reccomendations are attached for your reference.','9034'),(655,'To access 2006 Expert Working Group (EWG) meeting documents, click on the appropriate EWG in the sidebar to the left.','9057'),(656,'UPDATED: 23 August 2006\r\n\r\nAll documents received have now been posted. If you have any new items, please bring an electronic and hard copy to the meeting.\r\n\r\nThese documents have been provided by various experts, and some authors circulated their discussion papers directly in advance of the meeting. Additionally, Howard Pharo’s thesis is provided for background reading.\r\n\r\nI apologize for the short time you will have to review these documents but the time available was short with the SC approval processes and vacation schedules.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, the WTO-SPS representative is unable to attend the meeting.\r\n\r\nHave a safe trip and I look forward to seeing you on Monday.\r\n\r\nBrent Larson, Standards Officer, IPPC Secretariat','9047'),(657,'4 September 2006\r\n\r\nDear expert working group members,\r\n\r\nDocuments are being posted for the meeting as they become available. The documents list will be updated accordingly.\r\n\r\nPlease send any papers for posting to stacie.johnston@fao.org by 6 September 2006.\r\n\r\nCopies of documents will not be available at the meeting so please bring your own.\r\n\r\nBrent Larson will meet you in the hotel lobby at 9:30 Monday morning (11 September 2006) to take you to the meeting. If you are unable to be there at that time please take a taxi to the meeting venue.','9048'),(658,'25 September 2006\r\n\r\nDear expert working group members,\r\n\r\nI have posted the final draft ISPM and the presentations given at the meeting.\r\n\r\nIf there are any changes to be made to your contact information as presented in the participants list (Document 3), please send them to me (stacie.johnston@fao.org).','9049'),(659,'Document posting has been finalized: 24 October 2006- Close of day Rome: Make sure to print off an updated Document list Doc 02 Rev 02. If anyone would like to present an additional document please be sure to bring enough printed copies for the entire EWG. Have a safe trip and see you in Orlando.\r\n- Brent Larson, Standards Officer, IPPC\r\n\r\nI would encourage you to start with doument No. 12-Briefing paper for the meeting of the Expert Working Group on Specification No. 16, as this will provide you guidance to the discussion papers posted so far.\r\nPlease note that doc 16 is for reference only .\r\n\r\nPlease keep checking this page for updates or new documents, the final date for posting documents will be 25 October 2006.','9050'),(660,'The draft report and draft supplement produced during the meeting are now posted.','9051'),(661,'<p/>','10734'),(662,'The topic, Plants for planting (including movement, post-entry quarantine and certification programmes) was introduced into the International Plant Protection Convention’s (IPPC) standard setting work programme by the Interim Commission on Phytosanitary Measures at its seventh session in March 2005. Specification No. 34 was developed and approved by the Standards Committee, May 2006, and the suggested title was changed to Pest risk management for plants for planting in international trade.\r\n \r\nThe first meeting of the EWG Pest risk management for plants for planting in international trade took place 11-15 September 2006 in Ottawa, Canada. Partial text for a draft ISPM was developed and tasks were assigned to the EWG members. The EWG discussed the suggested title of the draft ISPM and decided to recommend the ISPM be called \"Elements of Plants for Planting Systems Approach\". \r\n \r\nThe second meeting was held in Vancouver, Canada on 26 February–2 March, 2007.  A draft standard was submitted to the SC for its May 2008 meeting.  The SC-7 discussed this draft and decided to return it for redrafting giving specific guidance for changes to be made.  The SC, at its November 2008 meeting, agreed that the standard could be redrafted with the input of two former EWG members, an additional member from the SC, a new member from South Africa and the Steward.  Accordingly, a meeting was arranged in December 2008 in Israel.\r\n \r\nThe Expert Working Group (EWG) met on December 17-19, 2008 at the Plant Protection and Inspection Services (PPIS), Ministry of Agriculture and Development, in Bet Dagan, Israel. The meeting was hosted by the NPPO of Israel and was opened by David Opatowski, Steward.','9130'),(663,'2008 expert working groups\r\n\r\nTo access documents for expert working group (EWG) meetings held in 2008, click on the appropriate EWG in the sidebar to the left.','9074'),(664,'Dear all,\r\nThe documents distributed during the meeting are now posted to this site. The draft report will be distributed by email.\r\n\r\nThe most updated Documents List is 02_Documents list_2008_01_31 (20 documents, all posted)\r\n\r\n31 January 2008\r\n\r\nDear EWG participants\r\n\r\nAll documents for the meeting have now been posted. In addition to the 20 working documents for the meeting, ISPMs No. 7 and No. 12 are also posted below (click \"view all\" to see all of the documents, as they are now split onto 2 pages due to the long list). \r\n\r\nWe wish you safe travels and look forward to meeting you in a few days.\r\n\r\n30 January 2008\r\n\r\nDear EWG participants,\r\n\r\n19 meeting documents are posted, and one additional document will by posted on Thursday, 31 January. Please remember to bring your own copies of the meeting documents. In the case that you wish to share any other document with the group, please bring 16 hard copies to share with all of the participants.\r\n\r\nAs noted in the email sent on 30 January, participants arriving at the Fresno airport between 11 and 13:30 should meet in the airport\"s conference room (when walking from the main lobby to the baggage claim, it is on the right side of the passageway). We look forward to meeting you all in a few days.\r\n\r\n28 January 2008\r\n\r\nDear all, \r\n\r\nAdditional documents have been posted today, and two papers submitted by the IPPC Secretariat will be posted shortly. An email with more detailed information regarding travel arrangements between the airport and Tenaya Lodge will also be circulated soon. Please contact sonya.hammons@fao.org with any questions you may have regarding the arrangments; we look forward to meeting you next week.\r\n\r\n25 January 2008\r\n\r\nDear EWG participants,\r\nDiscussion documents are being posted in the order received, along with an updated version of the Documents List. Please note that all participants are expected to bring their own copies of the meeting documents. Additional details regarding transportation from the airport will be emailed to the group next week (by Wednesday 30 January). We look forward to working with all of you in February.\r\n\r\n21 January 2008\r\n\r\nDear EWG participants,\r\n\r\nAs the meeting quickly approaches in just two weeks, please ensure that your hotel reservations are confirmed. If you will stay in Fresno on the evening of Friday, 8 February, please make sure that you are not also booked to stay in the Tenaya Lodge on the same night.\r\n\r\nWe would like to remind all participants that discussion papers for the EWG should be sent to brent.larson@fao.org and sonya.hammons@fao.org by this Friday, 25 January to allow for time to review the documents in the days before the meeting.\r\n\r\n14 January 2008\r\nDear EWG members,\r\n\r\nBest regards to all of you in this new year.\r\n\r\nAt this time each participant\"s hotel reservations should have been confirmed and paid for by the participant.\r\n\r\nPlease note that additional documents have been posted, as well as an updated documents list.\r\n\r\nWe look forward to receiving discussion papers as soon as possible, and no later than 25 January.\r\n\r\n21 December 2007\r\n\r\nDear expert working group members,\r\n\r\nWelcome to the online work area for the upcoming meeting on Revision of ISPMs 7 and 12 in California in February.\r\n\r\nLocal arrangements have been confirmed: the meeting will take place in Fish Camp, California, USA. Participants are advised to fly into Fresno Yosemite International Airport on Sunday, 3 February 2008 in order to allow for travel time to the meeting venue.\r\n\r\nHotel reservations have been made on your behalf, but each participant is responsible for confirming and paying for his/her room by 11 January 2008. After that the hotel will only provide rooms on a space-available basis, and at a higher rate.\r\n\r\nAdditional local information is provided in the document below.\r\n\r\nDocuments will be posted for the meeting as they become available, and the documents list will be updated accordingly.\r\n\r\nPlease send any papers for posting to brent.larson@fao.org. Additional questions may be sent to sonya.hammons@fao.org.\r\n\r\nCopies of documents will not be available at the meeting so please prepare a set of documents to bring with you.\r\n\r\nThe agenda and documents list will be revised several times throughout the coming weeks, with the date of the most recently posted version noted on the document title below.\r\n\r\nIf you note that your contact information as included in the participants list is incorrect, please inform sonya.hammons@fao.org of the necessary changes.\r\n\r\nThank you for participation; we look forward to meeting you in February.','9075'),(665,'Dear EWG members,\r\n\r\nWelcome to the online work area for the upcoming expert working group meeting on pre-clearance for regulated articles. Meeting documents will be posted to this site, so please check frequently.\r\n\r\nThe Secretariat of the IPPC invites discussion papers for review at the meeting. Please submit any discussion papers to Brent.Larson@fao.org (with a copy to Sonya.Hammons@fao.org) by 15 August 2008.\r\n\r\nPlease contact Brent.Larson@fao.org or Sonya.Hammons@fao.org with any queries you may have related to the meeting.\r\n\r\nThank you for your participation in the drafting process. We look forward to working with you.\r\n\r\nUpdate: Coordination of visas and airport transfers is being coordinated by Hazel.Chizyuka@fao.org - please forward your travel itinerary to Ms. Chizyuka so that transportation between the airport and Lilayi Lodge may be coordinated.\r\n\r\nMeeting documents have been posted and are available for download below.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the working documents, you are invited to refer to the published ISPMs. The specification for the EWG on pre-clearance refers to \"relevant ISPMs\". All of the published ISPMs are available for download on the IPP: \"https://www.ippc.int/id/13399?language=en\".\r\n\r\nPlease note that US dollars of denominations 2003 or more recent are accepted by the hotel, as well as credit cards.\r\n\r\nPlease bring your own set of documents to the meeting.','9076'),(666,'<p/>','9094'),(667,'<p/>','9095'),(668,'<p/>','9128'),(669,'![enter image description here][1]<p>Dear EWG members, Welcome to the expert working group (EWG) restricted work area for the upcoming EWG meeting on Plant Breeding Material. The meeting documents are already posted on this site and are available for download below. Please check regularly for new documents as there are updates of the existing ones or new posts. The Secretariat of the IPPC invites discussion papers for review at the meeting. Please submit any discussion papers to Ms. Lottie Erikson (Lottie.Erikson@fao.org) and Ms. Stephanie Dubon (Stephanie.Dubon@fao.org) by 22 January 2010. In addition to the working documents, you are invited to refer to the published ISPMs and other references as outlined in the Specification No. 45. All of the published ISPM are available for download on the IPP: https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=13399. Please bring your own set of documents to the meeting. Please contact Ms. Erikson and Ms. Dubon with any queries you may have related to the meeting. Thank you for your participation in the standard drafting process. We look forward to be working with you.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/8c09b2d2c3.jpg','9129'),(670,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\nWelcome to the expert working group (EWG) restricted work area for the upcoming EWG meeting on the Movement of soil and growing media in association with plants in international trade. Some meeting documents are already posted on this site and are available for download below. Please check regularly for new documents as there are updates of the existing ones or new posts. The Secretariat of the IPPC invites discussion papers for review at the meeting. Please submit any discussion papers and any supporting documents (regulations, journal articles, etc.) to Ms. Stephanie Dubon (Stephanie.Dubon@FAO.org) by 15 May 2010. In addition to the working documents, you are invited to refer to the published ISPMs and other references as outlined in the Specification No. 43. All of the published ISPMs are available for download on the IPP: https://www.IPPC.int/index.php?id=13399. Please bring your own set of documents to the meeting as we will not be able to provide copies at the meeting. Please contact Ms. Dubon with any questions you may have. Thank you for your participation in the standard drafting process and we look forward to working with you.\r\n\r\nWe are planning a field trip for Wednesday afternoon and a free dinner at the hotel Wednesday evening, 16 June, and a group dinner Thursday evening, 17 June.\r\n\r\nThe meeting will start at 10:00 a.m on the morning of Monday 14 June. Mr. Brent Larson of the IPPC Secretariat will transport everyone to the meeting venue and will leave the hotel at 9:00 a.m. sharp. If you are not in the hotel lobby at that time, you will need to take a taxi to the meeting venue. On Tuesday 15 June through Friday 18 June, Mr. Larson will leave the hotel at 8:30 am sharp. He will also return everyone to the hotel every day after the meeting.\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/6b2a3b6c09.jpg','9139'),(671,'<p/>','9164'),(672,'Please see Sea Containers <a href=\"work-area-pages/sea-containers-ewg/\">page</a>','9169'),(673,'Please see Sea Containers <a href=\"work-area-pages/sea-containers-ewg/\">page</a>','14667'),(674,'<p/>','26831'),(675,'<p/>','26832'),(676,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\n\r\n**Dear participants, WELCOME.**\r\n\r\n\r\n**Update: 2014-06-11:** 03_EWGCutFlowers_2014_June_ParticipantsList posted (updated version)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Update: 2014-06-02:** Documents posted today\r\n\r\n- 01_EWGCutFlowers_2014_June_ProvisionalAgenda (Updated on 2 June 2014)\r\n\r\n\r\n- 02_EWGCutFlowers_2014_June_ProvisionalDocumentsList\r\n\r\n\r\n- 04_EWGCutFlowers_2014_June_Rev1_LocalInformation\r\n\r\n\r\n_________\r\n\r\n**URGENT UPDATE (2014-05-23):**\r\n\r\n\r\nAs security issues in Kenya are becoming more of a concern, and several of the experts have informed us that their governments will not allow them to travel to Kenya, the IPPC Secretariat had to consider in holding this meeting in another country.\r\n\r\nThe Secretariat made the decision to hold this meeting in **Arusha, Tanzania** on the same dates of **16-20 June 2014**.\r\n\r\n\r\nFor those that need a personnel invitation letter to attend the meeting now in Arusha (Tanzania)and for apply to obtain a visa, please email to Ms Lahti at <Tanja.Lahti@fao.org> a.s.a.p.\r\n\r\n\r\nArusha is approximately 144.21 Miles / 232.09 Km distance from Nairobi. The Secretariat is not considering in providing terrestrial transfer from Nairobi to Arusha.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe closest airport to Arusha is Kilimanjaro (JRO airport). Please consider re-book your flight tickets.\r\nFor those that already got the flight ticket to Nairobi (NBO airport), please consider that there are airline companies that flies NBO-JRO with direct flights (1 hour). However, this might imply in two immigration checks. \r\n\r\n\r\nThe Secretariat will keep all the participants updated very soon.\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you for your attention and comprehension.\r\n\r\nRegards, \r\n\r\nThe IPPC Secretariat.\r\n\r\n\r\n_____________\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe EWG for the draft ISPM on International movement of cut flowers and branches (2008-005) will be held in **Kenya from 16 to 20 June 2014**. \r\n\r\nThe meeting will convene in Lake Naivasha Sawela Lodge in Lake Naivasha area, about 85 Kilometers from Nairobi. However, please note that an overnight stay is needed from 14 to 15 June in Nairobi. We recommend that your visa is requested for a period including at least two days before the meeting starts and two days after the meeting closes. More information is available in the Local information document posted below. \r\n\r\n\r\nThe approved specification 56 can be found below or by [clicking here](https://www.ippc.int/publications/specification-56-international-movement-cut-flowers-and-branches).\r\n\r\n\r\nThe deadline for submitting discussion papers to the IPPC Secretariat is **16 May 2014**. \r\nPlease, in the subject title insert \"EWG Cut Flowers - Discussion Paper\" and send to <adriana.moreira@fao.org> with copy to <mirko.montuori@fao.org>.\r\n\r\n\r\nYou are requested to download all meeting documents and bring them with you because they will not be made available at the meeting. Please check this webpage frequently for updates prior to the meeting.\r\n\r\n\r\nIf you have problems accessing the restricted area or downloading the documents, please contact Ms Paola Sentinelli <Paola.Sentinelli@fao.org>.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe also kindly ask you to bring some snacks from your home country, if possible, so we can have a diversity of tastes in our coffee-breaks. Thank you for this.\r\n\r\n\r\n_____________\r\n\r\n\r\n**UPDATES**\r\n\r\n- 2014-05-20: Documents 16, 17 and 18 posted. Also, updated agenda and documents list.\r\n\r\n- 2014-05-14: History of the topic on Cut Flowers and Branches and draft specification paper, prepared by the steward, posted.\r\n\r\n- 2014-02-26: Local information document posted.\r\n\r\n- 2014-02-24: Draft agenda, draft participants list and draft documents list posted.\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/fresh-cut-flowers1.jpg','27528'),(677,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\n**08 September 2014**\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Please note** that a new version of document no. 04 has been posted because there the previous version had issues with the page numberin.\r\n\r\n**05 September 2014**\r\n\r\nThree more documents have now been posted, along with an updated Agenda and Documents list.\r\n\r\nNo more documents will be posted before the meeting so please bring copies if you would like to share them with the group.\r\n\r\nRegards, Mike\r\n\r\n**31 August 2014**\r\n\r\nDear all,\r\n\r\nAll documents for the meeting have now been posted including updates to the Agenda and Documents list.\r\n\r\nPlease download all of these documents and review the contents before the meeting.  No printed copies will be provided.\r\n\r\nIf you have any further documents to share, please bring 9 printed copies to the meeting for distribution.\r\n\r\nPlease be reminded to bring picture ID (e.g. passport) for registration and come well in advance (09:00-15), in case there is a line. We will serve coffee at 09:30h so we can say hello before starting the meeting.\r\n\r\nRegards, Mike\r\n\r\n**05 August 2014**\r\n\r\nDear Members of the EWG for Wood Handicrafts,\r\n\r\nHopefully your preparations for the meeting of the working group are going well.\r\n\r\nI have sent you an excel spread sheet to capture your travel and hotel details so the IPPC Secretariat can find you if there are any problems. Please complete your line on each sheet and return to me before the end of the month if possible.\r\n\r\nIf you are having any difficulties with your travel arrangements please contact Mr Mirko Montuori (Mirko.Montuori@fao.org) and copy in Nuri Niyazi (Nuri.Niyazi@fao.org) to your message.\r\n\r\nAll documents for the meeting need to be sent to me by the end of next week for posting on the IPP.  I will let you know when all documents and final versions for the meeting have been posted on the IPP (below). You will then need to download the documents and bring a copy (a print-out or on your PC/Tablet) to the meeting.\r\n\r\nPlease feel free to contact me if you have any questions or need anything clarified for the meeting.\r\n\r\nRegards, Mike\r\n\r\n12 June 2014\r\n\r\nMeeting arrangement. The meeting is organized under the work programme of the CPM and will convene in FAO Headquarters in Rome, Italy. This is a five-day meeting and you are requested to make travel arrangements to arrive before the meeting begins (10:00 Monday morning) and depart after the meeting ends (17:00 Friday afternoon). Confirm your participation directly to Mr Eva Moller (Eva.Moller@fao.org) no later than 15 August 2014, in order to finalize local arrangements.\r\n\r\nLocal information. Mr Michael Ormsby will be the IPPC Secretariat contact for this meeting (Michael.Ormsby@fao.org). A document outlining all the local information, including hotel and airport information, is posted in the “EWG Wood” restricted work area on the International Phytosanitary Portal (IPP – link below).\r\n\r\nMeeting documents and preparation. Meeting documents are posted in the SC restricted work area on the IPP https://www.ippc.int/work-area-pages/ewg-wood-products-and-handicrafts (to access this area, please login on the IPP and paste the link in your browser). You are requested to download all meeting documents and bring them with you, as they will not be made available at the meeting. If you have problems accessing the restricted area or downloading the documents, please contact Ms Paola Sentinelli (Paola.Sentinelli@fao.org).\r\n\r\nA draft agenda will be posted shortly. Please send discussion papers to Michael.Ormsby@fao.org (with copy to Eva.Moller@fao.org) no later than 15 August 2014 so we can post them on the restricted work area.\r\n\r\nVisa. Please ensure that you make proper visa arrangements for travelling to Italy, if necessary. Attention is drawn to the strict provisions in force regarding entry into Italy, including the refusal of entry to persons not having the required visas. Participants requiring entry visas must obtain these from the Italian Consulate or Diplomatic Mission in their country before leaving for Italy.\r\n\r\nIPPC criteria for receiving travel assistance. Criteria used for prioritizing participants to receive travel assistance to attend meetings organized by the IPPC Secretariat was recently amended and full details on these criteria can be found on the IPP (https://www.ippc.int/publications/criteria-used-prioritizing-participants-receive-travel-assistance-attend-meetings).\r\n\r\nMembers requesting assistance may submit their requests directly to Ms Eva Moller (Eva.Moller@fao.org) no later than 15 August 2014.\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/wooden_handicrafts.jpg','27997'),(678,'<p/>','9017'),(679,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\n\r\n**Dear TPDP members, WELCOME to our work area!**\r\n\r\nTo access documents for TPDP meetings, click on the appropriate meeting in the menu to the right.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"warning floatcenter\">NEWS</a><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n**1) New updated version of the Instructions to Authors is now posted**\r\n\r\n2014-08-28: As it was agreed during the 2014 July TPDP meeting, **the Template tables for description of PCR,RT-PCR or PRC-RFLP reactions** was included to the Instructions for Authors as an **Appendix 5**.\r\n\r\n\r\n**2) The TPDP 2013-2014-2015 Work Plan is posted below**. \r\n\r\nPlease note the following deadlines to send back the documents below to the Secretariat as discussed during the last TPDP meeting. \r\n\r\n\r\n**By 15 August 2014**: \r\n\r\n- The contact details of the DP drafting group. \r\n- Templates for mix composition for PCR.\r\n- Feedback about establishing contact with some authors and members of DP drafting groups. \r\n- Draft DPs intended to go to the 2015 February member consultation (MC): \r\n\r\n            1. Sorghum halepense (2006-027) \r\n\r\n            2. Liriomyza spp. (2006-017) \r\n\r\n            3. Bursaphelenchus xylophilus (2004-016)\r\n\r\n            4. Xanthomonas fragariae (2004-012) \r\n\r\n            5. Xiphinema americanum sensu lato (2004-025)\r\n\r\n            6. Tomato spotted wilt virus, Impatiens necrotic spot virus, Watermelon siver mottle virus (2004-019)\r\n\r\n- Draft DP on Potato spindle tuber viroid (PSTVd) + responses to MC intended to be submitted to SC for approval for adoption. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**By 22 August 2014**: \r\n\r\n- Revision of the 2014 TPDP July meeting report.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**By 15 September 2014**: \r\n\r\n- Quality Assurance terms and definitions used in DPs.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease note that the work plan (version updated after the 2013 December TPDP virtual meeting) is posted below. More updated version will be posted later.\r\n\r\n\r\n**3) TPDP virtual meeting: September 2014**\r\n \r\nThe next TPDP virtual meeting will be either on September 3rd or 4th, 2014. The exact date with more information about the agenda will be posted later on the TPDP restricted page. \r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/tpdp_july_2014.jpg','9063'),(680,'TP Diagnostic Protocols 16-20 October 2006, Valencia, Spain\r\n9 November 2006\r\nI have now posted the revised versions of all the protocols and the draft report.\r\n\r\n24 October 2006\r\nDear TPDP members,\r\n\r\nI have posted the work programme and the Thrips palmi protocol as revised at the meeting. I will post additional documents from the meeting over the next few days.\r\n\r\nBest regards, Jane','9019'),(681,'**TP Diagnostic Protocols 24-28 September 2007, Buenos Aires, Argentina**\r\n3rd October\r\n\r\nI hope you had a safe journey home. I have posted the modified protocols that were worked on during the meeting with the label REV-01. I have also posted the work programme. Let me know if you require any other documents before I send the draft report.\r\n\r\nRegards, Jane','9068'),(682,'27 September 2007: One additional CV has been added and the compiled summary has been updated to include this information.\r\n\r\n\r\n21 September 2007: A revised version of the compiled summary has been posted.\r\n\r\n\r\n20 September 2007: A compiled summary of the DP author nominees has been posted.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe CVs below were submitted in response to the Secretariat\"s call for authors for specific diagnostic protocols in June 2007. The CVs of nominated authors will be posted as they arrive (update 20th September 2007: all CVs have been posted). PLEASE NOTE that in order to see all of the CVs you must click \"All\" at the bottom of this page.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nA call was made for authors for the following diagnostic protocols:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFungi and fungus-like organisms:\r\nFusarium moniliformis / moniforme syn. F. circinatum\r\nGymnosporangium spp. (authors with expertise from Asia and North America are needed)\r\nPuccinia psidii\r\n\r\n\r\nInsects and mites:\r\nBactrocera dorsalis complex\r\nDendroctonus ponderosae syn. Scolytus scolytus\r\nIps spp.\r\nLiriomyza spp.\r\nTephritidae: Identification of immature stages of fruit flies of economic importance by molecular techniques\r\n\r\n\r\nNematodes:\r\nAphelenchoides besseyi, A. ritzemabosi and A. fragariae\r\n\r\n\r\nPlants:\r\nSorghum halepense\r\n\r\n\r\nViruses and phytoplasmas:\r\nPotato spindle tuber viroid\r\nViruses transmitted by Bemisia tabaci','9071'),(683,'**TP Diagnostic Protocols 2-6 June 2008, Braunschweig, Germany**','9081'),(684,'**TP Diagnostic Protocols 2009 (work via electronic communication)**','9101'),(685,'08-11-2010: Final report of the meeting posted.\r\n\r\n01-09-2010: Posted powerpoint presentations and documents distributed during the meeting. Draft report is under review by rapporteur and will be circulated soon.\r\n\r\n19-07-2010 : 2010_TPDP_25 posted\r\n\r\n15-07-2010, Dear TPDP members and invited experts,\r\n- A few documents were added or updated below.\r\n- A few last documents will be posted before Tuesday 20 July.\r\n- We will meet at 8.45 in the hotel lobby on Monday to walk to the venue and get our badges together','9144'),(686,'![enter image description here][1]<p/>\r\n\r\n\r\n![TPDP members at their November 2012 meeting in Paris](../sites/default/files/pictures/tpdp-2012-11-paris.jpg)\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPicture above is of the TPDP members at their November 2012 meeting in Paris, France, hosted by EPPO.\r\n\r\nLeft to right: Mr Brendan Rodoni (AUS), Ms Adriana Moreira (IPPC), Mr Hans de Gruyter (NLD), Ms Ana Lía Terra (URY), Mr Delano James (CAN), Ms Liping Yin (CHN), Mr Robert Taylor (NZL), Mr Mallik Malipatil (AUS), Mr Colin Jeffries (GBR), Ms Geraldine Anthoine (FRA), Ms Jane Chard (GBR), Ms Fabienne Grousset (IPPC), Mr Norman Barr (USA), Ms Françoise Petter (EPPO).\r\n\r\n**********************************\r\n\r\nThe 2012 meeting of the TPDP will take place in Paris, France on 26-30 November 2012. The meeting will be hosted by the European and Mediterranean Plant Protection Organization.\r\n\r\n09-11-2012: posted **revised agenda** and revised **documents list**, plus **document 3** and **documents 29-34**\r\n08-10-2012: posted documents 20-28 plus revised agenda and documents\' list. The documents include draft DPs for Erwinia amylovora and Xanthomonas citri subsp. citri.\r\n26-09-2012: documents 14-19 plus revised agenda. The documents include the draft DP on potato spindle tuber viroid, a document on QA and a draft standardized format for DPs.  \r\n24-08-2012: documents 8-13 posted\r\n14-08-2012: documents 4-7 posted\r\n22-06-2012: provisional agenda posted\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/tpdp-2012-11-paris.jpg','9255'),(687,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\n**Dear TPDP members, WELCOME!**\r\n\r\n **Don&#39;t forget to bring some snacks from your country to our coffee-breaks** \r\n\r\nNo printed copies will be distributed at the meeting \r\n\r\n**Invited Experts:**\r\n\r\n- Ms Françoise PETTER (Host) \r\n- Ms Natasa MEHLE (Host - Invited Expert) \r\n- Ms Antoinette SWART (Invited Expert - Lead author Ditylenchus protocol) \r\n\r\nNew Participants List posted on 13 June. \r\n\r\nUPDATE 9: Documents 25 to 27, updated agenda and documents list have been posted on June 24, 2013.\r\n\r\nUPDATE 8: Documents 23 and 24, updated agenda and documents list have been posted on 19 June 2013. \r\n\r\nUPDATE 7: Documents 18 and 22, updated participants list and documents list have been posted on 11 June 2013. \r\n\r\nUPDATE 6: Documents 19 to 21 have been posted on 10 June 2013. \r\n\r\nUPDATE 5: Documents 12 to 17, updated agenda and documents list have been posted on 07 June 2013.\r\n\r\nUPDATE 4: Documents 6 to 11 posted on 3 June 2013.\r\n\r\nUPDATE 3: Draft DPs posted on 29 May 2013. \r\n\r\nUPDATE 2: Local information and doc. 05 posted on 27 May 2013. \r\n\r\nUPDATE 1: Provisional agenda and participants list posted on 24 May 2013.\r\n\r\n ************************************************************** \r\n\r\nOur 2013 TPDP meeting will be convened in **Paris, France, on 24-28 June 2013** and will be hosted by the **Secretariat of the European and Mediterranean Plant Protection Organization (EPPO)** at its headquarters in Paris (21 boulevard Richard Lenoir, 75011 Paris, France). The meeting is organized under the work programme of the Commission on Phytosanitary Measures (CPM). The IPPC Secretariat contact for this meeting is Ms Adriana Moreira (e-mail: <adriana.moreira@fao.org>; tel. (+39) 06 5705 55809). Thank you all for the good and hard work. Moving forward! Kind regards, The IPPC Standards Setting Secretariat. \r\n\r\n******************************** \r\n\r\n**Summary of contacts and deadlines** \r\n\r\n**Contacts:**\r\n\r\n - Meeting organization, documents, all other queries than listed below: adriana.moreira@fao.org \r\n- Registration system, letter for visa to France: eppomeetings@eppo.int \r\n- Funding assistance to attend meeting: eva.moller@fao.org \r\n- Problems with IPP work area: paola.sentinelli@fao.org \r\n\r\n**Deadlines:** \r\n\r\n- 10 May submitting documents (other than protocols) for the meeting \r\n- 10 May requests for funding assistance to attend the meeting \r\n- 27 April confirm the draft protocols to be discussed \r\n- 27 May submitting draft protocols for the meeting \r\n- 27 May completing the registration for the meeting \r\n- 27 May pre-book hotel registration</adriana.moreira@fao.org></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/2191dd94c5.jpg','9272'),(688,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\n**2013 February Virtual Meeting of the Technical Panel on Diagnostic Protocols** **2013 February 25th** **“GoToTraining”** **Meeting Objectives** - Update on diagnostic protocols (DPs) status - Update on DPs to SC for approval to CPs notification period (adoption on behalf of CPM) - Update on DPs to SC for approval to MC - Update on DPs to expert consultation - Review of experts associated with the work program (DP drafting group) & call for authors - TPDP work plan 2012-2013 update \r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/85e6abe9ba.jpg','14600'),(689,'<p/>![Forum image](../sites/default/files/pictures/1364900729_TPDP_Forum_Page_IPP_1.jpg) **Welcome to our new page on IPP TPDP work area! TPDP Forum page.** **This TPDP Forum page is for a better usage of the IPP on decision making by the TPDP members for the improvement of the panel^s activities.** This forum page allows members to make comments on a specific issue, with a general view, and also allow members to vote on polls when required. **For posting your comments** on a specific forum, please click on \"TPDP Discussion\" bottom below and then select the forum that you want to comment. Once inside the forum (e-decision) you want to comment write your message related to the forum’s question and then push the \"Post!\" bottom. Please, be clear and concise. Thank you. **NOTE**: Please note that all backgroud documents are in a separate subfolder under the TPDP Forum page [https://www.ippc.int/work-area-pages/tpdp-forum-background-documents] Click [here](/forums/tpdp-forum) to see the **FORUM Discussion**.','15395'),(690,'<p/>','20858'),(691,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\n**Dear TPDP members, WELCOME** \r\n\r\nOur 2014 TPDP meeting will be convened in **Paris, France, on 07-12 July 2014** and will be hosted by the Secretariat of the European and Mediterranean Plant Protection Organization (EPPO) at its headquarters in Paris (21 boulevard Richard Lenoir, 75011 Paris, France). \r\n\r\nPlease note this is a six days meeting. The meeting is organized under the work programme of the Commission on Phytosanitary Measures (CPM). The IPPC Secretariat contact for this meeting is Ms Adriana Moreira (e-mail: <adriana.moreira@fao.org>; tel. (+39) 06 570 55809). \r\n\r\nThe deadline for submitting the draft DPs and discussion papers to the Secretariat is **30 May 2014**. \r\n\r\nPlease make sure to meet the deadlines to ensure a good preparation for the meeting. The agreed date for the Secretariat to post the draft DPs is 06 June. \r\n\r\nIn the meantime, please consider the tasks and deadlines outlined in the work plan (posted on the TPDP restricted work area main page). You are requested to download all meeting documents and bring them with you because they will not be made available at the meeting. Please check this webpage frequently for updates prior to the meeting. \r\n\r\nThank you all for the good and hard work. Moving forward! \r\n\r\nKind regards, The IPPC Standards Setting Secretariat.\r\n\r\n____\r\n\r\nUpdates: \r\n\r\n\r\n- **2014-07-10:** The updated version of Citrus tristeza virus (2004-021) draft DP was reposted today. This version contains the DP drafting group responses to experts and referee\'s comments. \r\n\r\n  \r\n- **2014-07-08:** The presentation of **the General Overview of Draft Diagnostic Protocols and next steps** was posted today under the agenda item 4.1 as a support document for the meeting. \r\n\r\n- **2014-06-30:** Updated agenda posted today: New bullet point for discussion on \"PSTVd draft DP (2006-022): Addressing Member Comments\" under agenda item \"6.1 General overview of status of protocols\"\r\n\r\n\r\n- **2014-06-27:** The local information is reposted today to reflect the new EPPO building code entrance. The provisional agenda and document list were updated accordingly. \r\n\r\n\r\n- **2014-06-26:** Document number 25 \"TPDP SWOT and Gap analysis\" is posted today.\r\n\r\n\r\n- **2014-06-24:** Mr Dominique COLLINS and Mr Thomas PRIOR confirmed their attendance at the meeting for 8th and 10th July, respectively. However, Mr Mariano CAMBRA, Mr Thomas SCHRÖDER and Mr Mallik MALIPATIL will not be able to attend the meeting.\r\n\r\n\r\n- **2014-06-24:** All meeting documents were posted today regardless the document 25_TPDP_2014_Jul: TPDP SWOT and Gap analysis (agenda item 7.4). \r\n\r\nThe provisional agenda was updated: The previous agenda item **6.3 Priorities for Additional Diagnostic Protocols: Boeremia foveata** was removed from the agenda. \r\n\r\nThe participants list was updated.\r\n\r\n\r\n- **2014-06-13:** The following documents have been posted today:\r\n\r\nBursaphelenchus xylophilus (2004-016); Xiphinema americanumm (2004-025); Liriomyza spp. (2006-017)Sorghum halepense (2006-027); documents 03, 05-09 and revised 01 (Provisional agenda).\r\n\r\n\r\n- **2014-06-03:** Invitation letters sent to lead authors (as agreed at 2014 TPDP June Virtual Meeting):\r\n\r\n- Mr Mariano CAMBRA from Spain for draft DP on Citrus tristeza virus (2004-021)for the 08 July 2014\r\n\r\n- Mr Thomas SCHRÖDER from Germany for draft DP on Bursaphelenchus xylophilus (2004-016) for the 09 July 2014\r\n\r\n- Mr Thomas PRIOR from United Kingdom for draft DP on Xiphinema americanumm (2004-025) for the 10 July 2014\r\n\r\n- Mr Mallik MALIPATIL from Australia for draft DP on Genus Liriomyza (2006-017) for the 08 July 2014\r\n\r\n- Mr Dominique COLLINS from United Kingdom for draft DP on Genus Liriomyza (2006-017) for the 08 July 2014\r\n\r\n\r\n- **2014-05-29:** Provisional Agenda, provisional Participants List and Local Information document posted.\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/paris1.jpg','26472'),(692,'![<p/>][1]\r\n\r\n**Meeting Objectives:**\r\n\r\n**A) Update on diagnostic protocols (DPs) status:** \r\n\r\n- DPs approved by SC for adoption (on behalf of CPM) \r\n\r\n- DPs out of 2013 member consultation\r\n\r\n- DPs for SC approval for member consultation in 2014\r\n\r\n- DPs to be submitted to Experts Consultation on IPP in 2013/2014\r\n\r\n\r\n**B) Summary and authors selection:** \r\n\r\n- Liberibacter spp. / Liberobacter spp. on Citrus spp. (2004-010)\r\n\r\n- Liberibacter solanacearum (2013-001)\r\n\r\n- Conotrachelus nenuphar (2013-002)\r\n\r\n- Anguina spp. (2013-003)\r\n\r\n\r\n**C) Update from relevant Bodies: Up