.html\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Note that United Kingdom is not on GMT during summer.</span></a></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</span></span></span></span></div>\r\n</span></p>','9270'),(698,'Please register for TPFQ September 2012 Virtual Meeting on Monday, September 10, 2012 2:00 PM - 4:00 PM GMT at:\r\n\r\nhttps://student.gototraining.com/r/9135534595809111040\r\n\r\nAfter registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training. \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nI have uploaded some draft meeting documents including the proposed Agenda and a version of the minutes of the July meeting (that includes comments received as at 26 July).\r\n\r\nPlease take note of the documents required for the meeting in September and those responsible have them to me for posting at least one week before the meeting (Friday 31 August).\r\n\r\nUPDATE 04 September 2012\r\n\r\nSome further files uploaded or updated.  Please check this folder for new files the last working day before the meeting.\r\n\r\nUPDATE 09 September 2012\r\n\r\nAll files now uploaded.  No more will be added before the meeting.\r\n\r\nThanks, Mike\r\n\r\nIPPC Secretariat','9261'),(699,'Please register for TPFQ July 2012 Virtual Meeting on Friday, July 6, 2012 2:00 PM - 4:00 PM GMT at:\r\n\r\nhttps://student.gototraining.com/r/567519866584396288\r\n\r\nAfter registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training. \r\n\r\nAs discussed, the intention is to focus on the draft ISPM for the International Movement of Wood.\r\nPlease check the work programme to ensure you are up-to-date with your tasks.\r\nPlease also review the documents below before the meeting, adding items to the draft agenda or correcting participant information etc.\r\n\r\nSend any changes to documents or any further documents for the meeting to Michael.Ormsby@fao.org','9260'),(700,'Please register for TPFQ Virtual Meeting May 2012 on Wednesday, May 23, 2012 2:00 PM - 4:00 PM GMT at:\r\n\r\nhttps://student.gototraining.com/r/7430178865162965504\r\n\r\nAfter registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training (including a calender appointment).\r\n\r\nPlease also review the documents below before the meeting, adding items to the draft agenda or correcting participant information etc.\r\n\r\nSend any changes to documents or any further documents for the meeting to Michael.Ormsby@fao.org','9246'),(701,'Please register for TPFQ April 2012 Virtual Meeting on Monday, April 2, 2012 2:00 PM - 4:00 PM GMT at:\r\n\r\nhttps://student.gototraining.com/r/2644959124549243136\r\n\r\nAfter registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training.\r\n\r\nPlease also review the documents below before the meeting, adding items to the draft agenda or correcting participant information etc.\r\n\r\nSend any changes to documents or any further documents for the meeting to Michael.Ormsby@fao.org','9245'),(702,'Please register for February 2012 TPFQ Virtual Meeting on Thursday, February 23, 2012 11:00 PM - Friday, February 24, 2012 1:00 AM GMT\r\n\r\nOnce you register the system will send you a notification email with a person-specific link to the meeting. \r\n\r\nI will start the meeting (all going well) 30 minutes before time so you can attempt to join early if you would like to test things first.','9244'),(703,'This folder will hold general files supporting the work of the TPFQ panel.\r\n\r\nInformation about the GOTOMeeting system, and general documents such as SC updates and other correspondence will be included here.','9181'),(704,'**2010 Technical Panel on Forest Quarantine Meeting, 20-24 September 2010, Rome, Italy**\r\n\r\n![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\nSeptember 9, 2010 - The meeting documents are now posted below.\r\n\r\nPlease bring copies of the documents with you to the meeting.\r\n\r\nSome documents have been revised. Check the posting date to ensure you have the most recent document.\r\n\r\nIf there are additional documents that you wish to share with the panel, please bring a copy with you.\r\n\r\nThe meeting starts at 10AM on Monday September 20th in the Queen Juliana Room, B325, (third floor of Building B),  FAO Headquarters, Viale delle Terme di Caracalla, Rome\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/85c316726c.jpg','9145'),(705,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/a5b1c9e187.jpg','9109'),(706,'![enter image description here][1]\r\n\r\n\r\n**TP Forest Quarantine 13-17 July 2009, Nanjing, China**\r\n\r\n\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/7324971472.jpg','9102'),(707,'**TPFQ 2008 8-12 December 2008, Puerto Varas City, Chile**\r\n\r\nMeeting documents and information will be posted as they become available. Please note that participants are expected to bring their own set of meeting documents. The yellow arrows at the top of each column can be used to sort the list of documents by document number, agenda item, or date posted. \r\nIn addition to the documents posted below, the FAO publications listed on the following website may be of interest, and will be available in hard copy at the meeting: http://www.fao.org/forestry/28341/en/','9089'),(708,'![enter image description here][1]<p/>\r\n\r\n**TP Forest Quarantine 2-6 July 2007, Moscow, Russia**\r\n  [1]: /static/media/uploads/workareapages/030cd34107.jpg','9061'),(709,'**TP Forest Quarantine, 12-16 June 2006, New York, USA**\r\n\r\n21 June 2006\r\n\r\nThe revised versions of Debarking and ISPM No. 15 are now posted. Please send any additional documents for posting to stacie.johnston@fao.org.','9024'),(710,'Photos from TPFQ meetings, etc. are now stored on Flickr which provides a bit more space to keep pictures. You can access the pictures at: http://flickr.com/gp/54548160@N06/n8B29C\r\n\r\n ','9180'),(711,'<p/><p class=\"bodytext\">-----&nbsp;13&nbsp;February 2013 ----</p> <p class=\"bodytext\">Hello TPFQ,</p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana; color: black; font-size: 8pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-ansi-language: EN-NZ; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-bidi-font-family: ^Times New Roman^;\" lang=\"EN-NZ\">Please register for </span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana; color: black; font-size: 8pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-ansi-language: EN-NZ; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma;\" lang=\"EN-NZ\">TPFQ February 2013 Virtual Meeting on Monday, February 18, 2013 4:00 PM - 6:00 PM GMT at:</span>&nbsp;</p> <p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; background: white;\" class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: black; font-size: 11pt;\"><a title=\"blocked::https://student.gototraining.com/r/783024151109676800\" href=\"https://student.gototraining.com/r/783024151109676800\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\">https://student.gototraining.com/r/783024151109676800</span></a></span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\">After registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training.</p> <p class=\"bodytext\">Let me know if there are any further items for the agenda or any further documents that need to be added.</p> <p class=\"bodytext\">Piotr I will send you&nbsp;your documents directly.</p> <p class=\"bodytext\">Regards, Mike-------&nbsp;</p> <p class=\"bodytext\">&nbsp;</p> <p class=\"bodytext\"></p><div><p></p><table class=\"\" border=\"0\"> <thead> <tr class=\"head\"> <th class=\"header\"><p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">Location</span></p></th><th class=\"sep header\"><p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">Local time</span></p></th><th class=\"sep header\"><p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">Time zone</span></p></th><th class=\"sep header\"><p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">UTC off