utline-level: 2;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: black; font-size: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB;\">Glossary:</span></strong></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-outline-level: 2;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; color: black; font-size: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB;\">UTC <a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/time/aboututc.html\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/time/aboututc.html\" target=\"_blank\">Coordinated Universal Time</a> - the international basis for other time zones. Same time as for GMT (Greenwich Mean Time) and <a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/military/z.html\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/military/z.html\" target=\"_blank\">Zulu time</a>.</span>','14699'),(712,'<p/>************************ 31 May 2013 ********************* All documents are now loaded and ready for downloading. Please note that the following documents have been updated and posted today: TPFQ_2013_Jun_39 TPFQ_2013_Jun_44 You will note that the restricted area is closed from the morning of Tuesday 4th June (Rome time) so I recommend downloading these files now and printing off any hard copies you need. If you are happy to use electronic copies only (and have trouble downloading them from the IPP) I will have them saved to a flash drive and CD (as well as my computer) at the meeting. Cheers, Mike ************************ 30 May 2013 ********************* All of the documents now loaded (except perhaps 01 (agenda) and 02 (documents list)) are finals. Document 44 (Draft report for the May Virtual Meeting) should be posted before the close of Friday 31st May. You will note that the restricted area is closed from the morning of Tuesday 4th June (Rome time) so I recommend downloading these files now and printing off any hard copies you need. If you are happy to use electronic copies only (and have trouble downloading them from the IPP) I will have them saved to a flash drive and CD (as well as my computer) at the meeting. Cheers, Mike ************************ 29 May 2013 ********************* Please note that the following documents have been posted today: TPFQ_2013_Jun_05 TPFQ_2013_Jun_06 TPFQ_2013_Jun_27 TPFQ_2013_Jun_38 TPFQ_2013_Jun_39 TPFQ_2013_Jun_40 TPFQ_2013_Jun_41 TPFQ_2013_Jun_42 TPFQ_2013_Jun_45 TPFQ_2013_Jun_46 TPFQ_2013_Jun_47 Also note that the following documents have been adjusted to correct their agenda numbers: TPFQ_2013_Jun_09 TPFQ_2013_Jun_28 And the Agenda, Documents list, Participants list, and Local information document have all been updated as well. ************************ 22 May 2013 ********************* **Location** The meeting of the Technical Panel on Forest Quarantine will take place at the buildings of Federação de Agricultura e Pecuária do Pará (FAEPA) in Belém, Brazil. Please arrive in the building entrance at 9:30 am Monday, 10 June. Please note that the meeting will begin on Monday at 10:00 am and at 9:00 am the rest of the week. The meeting dress code is casual. However, you should bring one appropriate outfit for the group dinner, planned for Tuesday evening, 11 June. A half day field trip for the morning of Thursday, 13 July. Details will be announced during the meeting. **Arrival** Participants should arrange to fly to Belém (international airport **Aeroporto Val de Cães**) at least on the Sunday before the start of the meeting. **Airport transfer** To arrange the transfer service from the airport to the hotel please send <Tanja.Lahti@fao.org> an email with your flight numbers and arrival times, whether you need transfer for any other person and, if so, their name and correspondent flight number. We need this information by May 29th. ************************ 30 April 2013 ********************* Note: all documents were re-posted by the IPPC Secretariat to ensure correct formatting (no substantive changes were made). ************************ 26 April 2013 ********************* First set of files added below. Please have a look, identify gaps and find (if possible) documents to fill the gaps. Regards, Mike ','15394'),(713,'<p/><p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;\">******* 22 May 2013 ******</span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">Two files updated for meeting - document numbers 02 and 05.</span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;\">******* 29 April 2013 ******</span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">Files below updated for May virtual meeting.</span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;\">******* 26 April 2013 ******</span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;\">As agreed at the February virtual meeting of the panel, we will be having an April virtual meeting postponed to&nbsp;Thursday the 23rd&nbsp;May.</span>&nbsp;</p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;\">The documents for this meeting have been posted below.&nbsp; Please send through to me any further documents you consider are required for the meeting.</span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;\">We will be using Adobe Connect for this meeting (rather than GotoMeeting<a></a>).&nbsp; Instructions for setting up Adobe Connect on your computer are provided in document TPFQ_May_2013_00.</span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;\">The proposed times for the start of the 2 hour meeting are below.&nbsp; However I believe at least one member can not make these times so another time schedule may be necessary.&nbsp; This will mean that someone else&nbsp;will have the late night slot (:-).</span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;\">The most important issue for the panel at this time is to prepare and provide documents for the meeting in Brazil in June, which must be in&nbsp;by the 10th of May.&nbsp; So please consider what information we will need for the various&nbsp;tasks we have before us (treatment&nbsp;criteria, wood moisture content and MBr<a></a>) and start sending these through to be processed and posted in the meeting folder on the IPP<a></a>.</span></p> <p class=\"bodytext\">&nbsp;</p> <p class=\"bodytext\"></p><div><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;\"><p></p><table class=\"\" border=\"0\"> <thead> <tr class=\"head\"> <th class=\"header\"><p class=\"bodytext\">Location</p></th><th class=\"sep header\"><p class=\"bodytext\">Local time</p></th><th class=\"sep header\"><p class=\"bodytext\">Time zone</p></th><th class=\"sep header\"><p class=\"bodytext\">UTC offset</p></th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr class=\"c0 odd\"> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=256 blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=256 Current local time in Vancouver\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=256\" target=\"_blank\">Vancouver</a> <span class=\"small\">(Canada - British Columbia)</span></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Thursday, 23&nbsp;May 2013 at 8:00:00 a.m.</p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/na/pdt.html blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/na/pdt.html Pacific Daylight Time\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/na/pdt.html\" target=\"_blank\">PDT</a></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">UTC-7 hours</p></td> </tr> <tr class=\"c1 even\"> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=232 blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=232 Current local time in Santiago\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=232\" target=\"_blank\">Santiago</a> <span class=\"small\">(Chile)</span></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Thursday, 23&nbsp;May 2013 at 1