blank\">BRT</a></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">UTC-3 hours</p></td> </tr> <tr class=\"c0 odd\"> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=4 blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=4 Current local time in Accra\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=4\" target=\"_blank\">Accra</a> <span class=\"small\">(Ghana)</span></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Thursday, 23&nbsp;May 2013 at 3:00:00 p.m.</p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/africa/gmt.html blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/africa/gmt.html Greenwich Mean Time\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/africa/gmt.html\" target=\"_blank\">GMT</a></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">UTC</p></td> </tr> <tr class=\"c1 even\"> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=37 blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=37 Current local time in Berlin\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=37\" target=\"_blank\">Berlin</a> <span class=\"small\">(Germany - Berlin)</span></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Thursday, 23&nbsp;May 2013 at 5:00:00 p.m.</p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/eu/cest.html blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/eu/cest.html Central European Summer Time\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/eu/cest.html\" target=\"_blank\">CEST</a></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">UTC+2 hours</p></td> </tr> <tr class=\"c0 odd\"> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=248 blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=248 Current local time in Tokyo\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=248\" target=\"_blank\">Tokyo</a> <span class=\"small\">(Japan)</span></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Midnight Thursday, 23&nbsp;May 2013 to 2&nbsp;a.m. (Friday 23rd)&nbsp;</p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/asia/jst.html blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/asia/jst.html Japan Standard Time\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/asia/jst.html\" target=\"_blank\">JST</a></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">UTC+9 hours</p></td> </tr> <tr class=\"c1 even\"> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=264 blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=264 Current local time in Wellington\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=264\" target=\"_blank\">Wellington</a> <span class=\"small\">(New Zealand)</span></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Friday, 24&nbsp;May 2013 at 3:00:00 a.m.</p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/pacific/nzst.html blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/pacific/nzst.html New Zealand Standard Time\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/pacific/nzst.html\" target=\"_blank\">NZST</a></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">UTC+12 hours</p></td> </tr> <tr class=\"c0 odd\"> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=215 blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=215 Current local time in Rome\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=215\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Rome</span></a> <span class=\"small\">(Italy)</span></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Thursday, 23&nbsp;May 2013 at 5:00:00 p.m.</p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/eu/cest.html blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/eu/cest.html Central European Summer Time\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/eu/cest.html\" target=\"_blank\">CEST</a></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">UTC+2 hours</p></td> </tr> <tr class=\"c1 even\"> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=262 blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=262 Current local time in Warsaw\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/city.html?n=262\" target=\"_blank\">Warsaw</a> <span class=\"small\">(Poland)</span></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Thursday, 23&nbsp;May 2013 at 5:00:00 p.m.</p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\"><a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/eu/cest.html blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/eu/cest.html Central European Summer Time\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/library/abbreviations/timezones/eu/cest.html\" target=\"_blank\">CEST</a></p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">UTC+2 hours</p></td> </tr> <tr class=\"c0 odd\"> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Corresponding&nbsp;UTC (GMT)</p></td> <td><p class=\"bodytext\">Thursday, 23&nbsp;May <a title=\"blocked::http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?iso=20130422T1500\" href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?iso=20130422T1500\" target=\"_blank\">2013 at 15:00:00</a></p></td> </tr> </tbody> </table><p class=\"bodytext\"></p></span></div><p></p>','15640'),(714,'Dear TPFQ,\r\n\r\nThe URL for the TPFQ virtual meeting on the 18th July using Adobe Connect is:\r\n\r\nhttp://fao.adobeconnect.com/r1dbbfq2k9l/\r\n\r\nThe instructions for connecting to and setting up your microphone etc are in document number 00 for the meeting.\r\n\r\nThe times for the meeting are given below.\r\n\r\nI will endeavor to enter the virtual meeting room 30 minutes before the meeting.\r\n\r\nRegards, Mike\r\n\r\nAs agreed at the Brazil meeting of the panel in June, we will be having a July virtual meeting on the 18th.\r\n\r\nThe documents for this meeting have been posted below. Please send through to me any further documents you consider are required for the meeting.\r\n\r\nWe will again be using Adobe Connect for this meeting. Instructions for setting up Adobe Connect on your computer and connecting to the meeting are provided in document TPFQ_2013_Jul_00.\r\n\r\nThe proposed times for the start of the 2 hour meeting are below.\r\n\r\nThe most important issue for the panel at this time is to review and agree to the report of the meeting in Brazil in June. There were also a number of tasks on the agenda of the Brazil meeting that we were unable to consider. We will need to set these tasks into the work programme for the coming year. So please consider what information we will need for the various tasks we have before us (e.g. wood moisture content and MBr, explanatory document, IFQRG/TPFQ work plan etc) and start sending these through to be processed and posted in the meeting folder on the IPP.\r\n\r\nThese are the corresponding times for your meeting:\r\n\r\nVancouver (Canada - British Columbia) Thursday, 18 July 2013 at 8:00:00 a.m. PDT UTC-7 hours\r\n\r\nSantiago (Chile) Thursday, 18 July 2013 at 11:00:00 a.m. CLT UTC-4 hours\r\n\r\nOttawa (Canada - Ontario) Thursday, 18 July 2013 at 11:00:00 a.m. EDT UTC-4 hours\r\n\r\nSão Paulo (Brazil - São Paulo) Thursday, 18 July 2013 at 12:00:00 Noon BRT UTC-3 hours\r\n\r\nAccra (Ghana) Thursday, 18 July 2013 at 3:00:00 p.m. GMT UTC\r\n\r\nBerlin (Germany - Berlin) Thursday, 18 July 2013 at 5:00:00 p.m. CEST UTC+2 hours\r\n\r\nTokyo (Japan) Midnight between Thursday, 18 July 2013 and Friday, 19 July 2013 JST UTC+9 hours\r\n\r\nWellington (New Zealand) Friday, 19 July 2013 at 3:00:00 a.m. NZST UTC+12 hours\r\n\r\nRome (Italy) Thursday, 18 July 2013 at 5:00:00 p.m. CEST UTC+2 hours\r\n\r\nWarsaw (Poland) Thursday, 18 July 2013 at 5:00:00 p.m. CEST UTC+2 hours\r\n\r\nCorresponding UTC (GMT) Thursday, 18 July 2013 at 15:00:00\r\n\r\nGlossary UTC - Coordinated Universal Time - the international basis for other time zones. Same time as for GMT (Greenwich Mean Time) and Zulu time. Note that United Kingdom is not on GMT during summer.','26603'),(715,'Dear TPFQ,\r\n\r\nAs agreed at the July virtual meeting of TPFQ, the date for the next TPFQ virtual meeting is the 2nd of October.\r\n\r\nOnly a few of you have commented on the two documents provided for comment on the TPFQ forum page on the IPP. Could everyone please comment on these documents by Friday (27th September) so I can close these fora and finalise the documents.\r\n\r\nThe TPFQ forum page is: https://www.ippc.int/forums/tpfq-forum-0\r\n\r\nThe URL for the TPFQ virtual meeting on the 2nd October using Adobe Connect is:\r\n\r\nhttp://fao.adobeconnect.com/r2y163btyd3/\r\n\r\nThe instructions for connecting to and setting up your microphone etc are in document number 00 for the meeting.\r\n\r\nThe times for the meeting are given below.\r\n\r\nI will endeavor to enter the virtual meeting room 30 minutes before the meeting.\r\n\r\nIf you have never attended an Adobe Connect meeting before:\r\n\r\nTest your connection: http://www.adobe.com/products/adobeconnect.html\r\n\r\nThe initial documents for this meeting will have been posted by Monday 30th September on the IPP at the following link (once you have logged in):\r\n\r\nhttps://www.ippc.int/work-area-pages/2013-october-virtual-meeting\r\n\r\nPlease send through to me any further documents you consider are required for the meeting.\r\n\r\nThe proposed times for the start of the 2 hour meeting are below.\r\n\r\nThese are the corresponding times for your meeting:\r\n\r\nLocation\r\n\r\nVancouver (Canada - British Columbia) Wednesday, 2 October 2013 at 8:00:00 a.m.\r\n\r\nSantiago (Chile) Wednesday, 2 October 2013 at 12:00:00 Noon\r\n\r\nOttawa (Canada - Ontario) Wednesday, 2 October