=\"color: black;\"><em>22-26 August 2011,&nbsp;</em></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><em>Hotel Vila Rica, Avenida Boa Viagem, 4308, Recife, Brazil</em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 9pt; text-align: left;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 9pt; text-align: left;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Update 8 August 2011</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 9pt; text-align: left;\" align=\"left\">The following documents were posted on 8 August:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document 01: Revised Agenda</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document 02: Revised Documents List</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document 05: Revised Updates from other relevant bodies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Update 5 August 2011</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 9pt; text-align: left;\" align=\"left\">The following documents were posted on 5 August:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Document 01: Revised Agenda</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Document 02: Revised Documents List</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Document 03: Revised Participants List</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Document 2004-022:&nbsp;Draft ISPM Systems approach for pest risk management of fruit flies (Tephritidae)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Update 2 August 2011</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Ms Lara Beany (<a href=\"mailto:lara@moscamed.org.br\">lara@moscamed.org.br</a>) has also sent hotel reservation information participants. Please contact her if you have any questions or have not received your hotel reservation information.</p>\r\n<p>The following documents were posted on 2 August:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Document 01: Revised Agenda</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Document 02: Revised Documents List</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Document 03: Revised Participants List</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Document 05: Updates from other relevant bodies</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Document 10: Revised Layout of the collection of fruit fly ISPMs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<!--[if !supportLists]-->\r\n<p><strong>Update 19 July 2011</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The meeting is organized under the work programme of the CPM. The Joint Division of the Food and Agriculture Organization and International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) has offered to host this meeting in Recife, Pernambuco, Brazil, from 22-26 August 2011. Please note that this is a five day meeting starting on Monday morning (09:00) and ending on Friday evening (17:00). Participants are requested to make their travel arrangements accordingly to ensure they are present for the entire meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">You will also receive a formal invitation from IAEA to participate in the meeting. This will include instructions on local arrangements and, where appropriate, funding arrangements for travel and daily subsistence allowance. <span style=\"layout-grid-mode: line;\">Please ensure that you make proper visa arrangements if necessary.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-outline-level: 1;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"layout-grid-mode: line; font-family: \" lang=\"EN-GB\">Mr Rui Pereira (</span><span style=\"color: black;\"><a href=\"mailto:r.cardoso-pereira@iaea.org\">r.cardoso-pereira@iaea.org</a></span><span style=\"layout-grid-mode: line; font-family: \" lang=\"EN-GB\">) is the main contact for this meeting. He will be in touch with you in advance of the meeting regarding documents.</span><span style=\"font-family: \" lang=\"EN-GB\"> The main aim of the meeting is to develop a draft annex to ISPM 26:2006 entitled &ldquo;Establishment and maintenance of fruit fly quarantine areas within a pest free area in the event of outbreak detection&rdquo;<span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"layout-grid-mode: line; font-family: \" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"layout-grid-mode: line; font-family: \" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Discussion papers should be forwarded to Mr Pereira <strong>no later than 16 July 2011</strong> so that they can be added to the agenda and posted on the work area. Please also note the tasks outlined in the <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">report of the last meeting (available at: <a href=\"/node/6181\">2010 TPFF Meeting Report (Vienna, Austria)</a> )</span>. </span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;\"> </span></p>','9188'),(721,'<p/>','9107'),(722,'<p/>','9105'),(723,'**Technical panel on fruit flies 1-5 September 2008, Vienna, Austria**\r\n\r\n**10 September 2008**\r\n\r\nDear colleagues,\r\n\r\nI\"ve posted the systems approach draft as finished in the meeting on Friday, and will send the report as soon as I can.','9083'),(724,'**TP Fruit Flies 03-07 December 2007, Vienna, Austria**\r\n\r\nPlease remember to bring the invitation letter sent to you by IAEA to the meeting on Monday as you will need it to get your building pass. It is recommended that you arrive at the IAEA building on Monday morning at 08:15 to allow sufficient time to get your pass.\r\n\r\n**28 November 2007**\r\n\r\nSome additional documents have been posted for the upcoming meeting (documents 11-15, and an updated documents list). Please excuse the late posting, we will make them available at the meeting.\r\n\r\n**14 November 2007**\r\n\r\nDocuments for the upcoming being are now being posted. Please check this page often as new documents will be added in the coming days. The documents list will be updated each time new documents are posted to reflect the updates.\r\n\r\nSpecial note: The reference document posted is very large (238 pages).\r\n\r\nParticipants are asked to download and bring their own sets of documents to the meeting.','9067'),(725,'**TP Fruit Flies 4-8 September 2006, Salvador, Brazil**','9018'),(726,'<p/>','9239'),(727,'<p/>','10735'),(728,'<p/>','10736'),(729,'**Technical Panel for the Glossary (TPG)**\r\n\r\n\r\nThis page contains the work plan and generic procedures. To access documents for individual TPG meetings, click on the appropriate meeting in the menu to the right.\r\n\r\n**01-07-2013** Updated work plan 2013-2014. The next meeting is confirmed for 10-14 February 2014, in FAO, Rome.','9035'),(730,'<p/>','10737'),(731,'<p/>','10738'),(732,'<p/>','10739'),(733,'**Technical panel on the Glossary 13-17 October 2008, Copenhagen, Denmark**\r\n\r\n10 October 2008\r\n\r\nThe comments on the definitions in the draft ISPM on potatoes have been posted (document 54). Please update your agenda and documents list accordingly.\r\n\r\n9 October 2008\r\n\r\nThe comments on the amendments to the glossary and supplement on CBD terminology have been posted (documents 52 and 53). The agenda and documents list have been updated accordingly (documents 1 and 2).','9085'),(734,'**Technical panel on the Glossary 15-19 June 2009, Rome, Italy**\r\n\r\nThe meeting will focus on reviewing inconsistencies in terms and style for International Standards on Phytosanitary Measures (ISPMs).\r\nThe report of the meeting and tables showing inconsistencies were posted on 06 July 2009.','9104'),(735,'<p><strong>07-10-2010 </strong>Posted 40, updated agenda and documents list<br /><strong>05-10-2010 </strong>Posted 39, updated agenda and documents list<br /><strong>03-10-2010 </strong>Posted 36, 37, 38, updated agenda and documents list<br /><strong>01-10-2010 </strong>Posted 35. agenda and documents list version 8.<br /><strong>24-09 </strong>Posted 27rev, 33 and 34. <strong>Please note change of meeting rooms as indicated on agenda v7</strong><br /><strong>23-09-2010 </strong>Posted document 32.<br /><strong>17-09-2010 </strong>Posted documents 29-31.<br /><strong>01-09-2010 </strong>Posted documents 24-28. Please confirm your participation to the meeting. Thank you<br /><strong>11-08-2010 </strong>Dear all, documents are posted up to 23. Please refer to the agenda for deadlines. A few questions were sent on agenda 7 (explanations of glossary terms). This point is still open even if a first document has been posted (doc 21)<br /><strong>19-07-2010 </strong>Dear all, I just posted documents 7 to 13. Doc 7 contains consistency amendments noted by CPM-5, and you might need it for preparing documents under agenda item 5.<br /><strong>24-06-2010 </strong>Dear all, invitation and agenda&nbsp;posted. Please check the agenda for deadlines.</p>','9165'),(736,'<p><strong>28-10-2011. </strong>Not widely distributed: steward\'s versions posted, as REV1 of documents 7 and 20. Also posted adjusted agenda, list of documents and participants list.</p>\r\n<p><strong>24-10-2011. </strong>Documents 27-28 posted</p>\r\n<p><strong>17-10-2011.</strong> Documents 21-26 posted (and version 4 of the agenda).</p>\r\n<p><strong>10-10-2011.</strong> Documents 18-20 posted (and version 3 of the agenda). This includes member comments on amendments to the glossary and on not widely distributed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>27-09-2011.</strong> First documents posted. The list of documents will be prepared later. Please check the site regularly for new additions.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Date and venue.</strong> 4-5 November 2011, Canada Room, FAO Rome.</p>','9223'),(737,'<p>The meeting of the TPG will take place in FAO, Rome, Italy on 15-19 October 2012 in the Espace Gabon room (A024)</p>\r\n<p><strong>9 October.</strong> last posting: revised agenda, documents list and participants list. Documents 37-39 have also be posted.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>3 October. </strong>posted revised Agenda and Documents list. Documents 3, 32-36 have also been posted.<br /><strong>12 September. </strong>posted revised Agenda and Documents list, revised document 21 and also posted all ISPMs again with agenda item numbers. Additionally, documents 28-31 have been posted today.<br /><strong>21 August.</strong> posted an amended version of document 22.<br /><strong>20 August.</strong> posted documents 22-27 and updated agenda with document numbers.<br /><strong>17 August.</strong> Posted documents 17-21, as well as draft ISPMs for member consultation, for the review of consistency in the use of terms under agenda item 4.<br /><strong>9 August</strong>. Posted documents 14 to 16.<br /><strong>22 June</strong>: posted updated work plan. Please check tasks and deadlines.<br />posted agenda and a first set of documents. Others will follow from 1 August 2012.</p>','9236'),(738,'<p/>','9237'),(739,'2012-12-27: We are beginning to post documents, please check this work area regularly.\r\n\r\n2013-01-10: We have now posted documents 14-17.\r\n\r\n2013-01-16: We have now posted documents 18-21.\r\n\r\n2013-01-23: We have now posted documents 22-24 and draft ISPMs 2005-003, 2005-010, 2006-029, 2005-004 (document numbers related to these documents were changed).\r\n\r\nNote: Agenda and Documents list were revised on 2013-01-19 and on 2013-01-24 (current version).','9271'),(740,'<b>7 October </b> <br>\r\nDocument 18 and version 4 of the agenda have been posted. Few other documents will be available at the meeting.<br>\r\n<b> 27 September 2009 </b> <br>\r\nThe draft agenda and some documents are posted. Most other documents will be posted in the week just before the meeting. Please check this work area.<br>\r\n<b> 09 September 2009 </b> <br>\r\nA general letter of invitation to this meeting has gone out today and individual letters will follow. I am in the process of hiring a consultant to manage this meeting and hope to have more information on this in the next few days.In the mean time I will be the IPPC contact for this meeting<br><br>\r\nKind regards, Brent','9110'),(741,'2014-05-13 We posted the TPG responses to MC comments.\r\n\r\n2014-02-04 A revised version of the Arabic translations of the Amendments to the Glossary (Document 1994-001_Ar Rev.1) was posted.\r\n\r\n2014-01-24 Today we posted the last documents for the TPG meeting: documents 33-34, the draft ISPM on seed and a revised agenda and documents list.\r\n\r\n2014-01-14 Today we posted documents 3, 28-32, 2006-004_UsedEquip, revised Agenda and Documents list.\r\n\r\n2014-01-09 Today we posted documents 1994-001 Ar, Ru and Zh; and documents 23-27.\r\n\r\n2013-12-09 Today we posted several documents, others we hope to publish before Christmas. To order the documents by agenda item number, please click on \"Agenda item\".','27100'),(742,'**2014-09-08**\r\n\r\nDear TPG members, Today I have posted the agenda for our meeting to be held at FAO HQ, Rome, from 8 to 12 December this year.\r\n\r\nPlease be reminded that discussion papers are due on 8 October 2014.\r\n\r\nBest, Eva','28157'),(743,'**Technical panel on phytosanitary treatments (TPPT)**','9066'),(744,'Dear TPPT Members,\r\n\r\nThe 2013 TPPT Meeting is scheduled for 8-12 July 2013 in Fukuoka, Japan.\r\n\r\nDo not hesitate to contact Artur.Shamilov@fao.org or Stephanie.Dubon@fao.org for questions about the meeting.\r\n\r\nPlease contact Mr Shibata Nobuyuki (nobuyuki_shibata@nm.maff.go.jp) for any questions regarding travel, hotels, etc.\r\n\r\nUPDATE: 27 June 2013\r\n\r\nAll meeting documents that I received have been posted below.\r\n\r\nPlease be kindly informed that due to some documents provided by submitters are heavy they will appear as the links and you will requested to download zip file.\r\n\r\nIf you will be presenting documents (discussion papers, revised checklists, etc.) other than those posted below, please send it to Artur.Shamilov@fao.org as soon as possible.\r\n\r\nThe draft agenda also which posted below last updated 27 June 2013.\r\n\r\nI look forward to seeing everyone on Monday morning, 8 July, at 10:00 am in Fukuoka.\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n\r\nArtur','9273'),(745,'<p/>','9274'),(746,'**Please register for 2013 February TPPT Virtual Meeting on Thursday, February 28, 2013 6:00 AM - 8:00 AM USA EST at:\r\nhttps://student.gototraining.com/r/222440345930557952**\r\n\r\nAfter registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training.\r\n\r\nApproximate meeting times are:\r\n\r\nLate evening: Australia and New Zealand Mid-day: Europe and Africa Early morning: North and South America\r\n\r\nI posted the agenda and all meeting documents below (except update relating TPPT position paper on adult emergence in irradiation which will be posted next week). Please email Artur Shamilov or Stephanie Dubon if you have any questions about the meeting.\r\n\r\nIn the case I have any updates relating our meeting I will inform you immediately.','9275'),(747,'The following documents are uploaded to this page. If you have a more recent version you would like to post, please send it to stephanie.dubon@fao.org. If you have comments on the drafts, please send them to the author and copy stephanie.dubon@fao.org and larry.zettler@fao.org.\r\n\r\nGuidance Documents\r\n\r\nTPPT_Guideline_A: Guidance for submitting treatments regarding soil and growing media associated with plants (CANNON/JESSUP)\r\nTPPT_Guideline_B: Guidelines: Cold Treatments (JESSUP/WILLINK/BAXTER)\r\nTPPT_Guideline_C: Guidelines: Vapour Heat Treatments (PARK)    \r\nTPPT_Guideline_D: Guidelines: Forced Air Heat Treatments (ORMSBY)     \r\nTPPT_Guideline_E: Guidelines: Hot Water Treatments (CANNON/WOOD)  \r\nTPPT_Guideline_F: Guidelines: Cold Treatment for Fruit (WOOD)   \r\nTPPT_Guideline_H: Guidelines: TPPT Criteria for Treatment Evaluation (ORMSBY)','9230'),(748,'Below is the latest version of the draft phytosanitary treatments under the TPPT work programme that have been submitted to the Secretariat and a zip file of all relevant documentation that the Secretariat has received since last TPPT face-to-face meeting. The Treatment Lead is indicated at the end of the title.\r\n\r\nThere are currently 19 treatments under the TPPT work Programme. As you also know there 5 new ISPMs on treatment requirements were added by the CPM-9 to the TPPT work programme.\r\n\r\nFor your better navigation I would like to inform you that the new received information within forlder can be found by the receiving date (for example 2010-106_SubmitterResponse_**2014-04-22**).\r\n\r\nThe latest version of Draft schedules also can be found by date of last modification (for example 2007-206A_DraftISPM_CTCeratitisCapitataCitrusSinensis_En_**2014-04-22**).\r\n\r\nIf you have a more recent version of the draft or other relevant documents not included in the zip files, please send them to Artur Shamilov : The list of phytosanitary treatments will be updated as needed after each SC meetings in May and November to reflect changes made by SC. @fao.org>','9177'),(749,'The 2012 TPPT Meeting is scheduled for 3-7 December 2012 in Nagoya, Japan.\r\n\r\nDo not hesitate to contact Stephanie.Dubon@fao.org or Larry.Zettler@fao.org for questions about the meeting.\r\n\r\nPlease contact Mr Kazutaka Ishii (kazutaka_ishii@nm.maff.go.jp) for any questions regarding travel, hotels, etc.\r\n\r\nUPDATE: 22 November\r\n\r\nAll meeting documents that I received have been posted below.\r\n\r\nIf you will be presenting documents (discussion papers, revised checklists, etc.) other than those posted below, please send it to Stephanie.dubon@fao.org AND bring 15 paper copies with you to meeting. \r\n\r\nPlease refer to the draft agenda (also posted below) for more information.\r\n\r\nI look forward to seeing everyone on Monday morning, 3 December, at 10:00 am in Nagoya.','9235'),(750,'<p/>','9234'),(751,'Please register for 2012 September TPPT Virtual Meeting on Wednesday, September 12, 2012 6:00 AM - 8:00 AM EDT (USA East Coast Time) at: https://student.gototraining.com/r/8841630740575931136\r\n\r\nAfter registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training. \r\n\r\nThe meeting is on Wednesday, 12 September 2012:\r\n\r\nLate evening: Australia and New Zealand\r\nMid-day: Europe and Africa\r\nEarly morning: North and South America\r\nNOTE THIS MEETING OCCURS AT A DIFFERENT TIME THAN OUR LAST FEW VIRTUAL MEETINGS, PER REQUEST OF SOME MEMBERS.\r\n\r\nLarry and I will be posting the agenda and all meeting documents below. Please email us if you have any questions about the meeting.','9233'),(752,'21 May 2012\r\n\r\nPlease register for 2012 May TPPT Virtual Meeting on Thursday, May 31, 2012 12:00 AM - 2:00 AM CEST (Wednesday night, Thursday morning, midnight Rome Time) at: https://student.gototraining.com/r/823136528285210112  \r\n\r\nAfter registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training. \r\n\r\nThe meeting will be 30/31 May:\r\n\r\nThursday morning 31st May for Asia, Australia and New Zealand\r\nWednesday night 30th May for Europe, Near East and Africa\r\nWednesday afternoon/evening 30th May for North and South America','9232'),(753,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Please register for February 2012 TPPT Virtual Meeting on Thursday, February 16, 2012 24:00 PM (midnight Rome time) - Friday, February 17, 2012 01:00 AM CET at:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><a href=\"https://student.gototraining.com/r/5544172274351384576\">https://student.gototraining.com/r/5544172274351384576</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"color: red;\">Please note the meeting will be Friday morning for New Zealand, Australia, Indonesia and China, Thursday night at midnight in Rome, Thursday evening in the eastern US/Argentina and Thursday afternoon in BC, Canada.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">After registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The meeting documents are posted below. Let myself or Larry know if you have any questions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','9231'),(754,'<p><strong>Update 2011-11-22</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<div><strong>The following documents were posted:</strong></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>2006-110: Draft annex to ISPM 28:2007: Vapour heat treatment of <em>Cucumis melo</em> var. <em>reticulatus</em> for <em>Bactrocera cucurbitae</em></li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Dec_05: TPPT Response to member comments</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Update 2011-11-21</strong></p>\r\n<p>Please register for 2011 December TPPT Virtual Meeting on <strong>Friday, December 2, 2011 00:00 AM - 2:00 AM (Friday morning ROME TIME) at</strong>: <a href=\"https://student.gototraining.com/r/7807125532375828224\">https://student.gototraining.com/r/7807125532375828224</a>. After registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please note this meeting is a 12-hour time difference from our regular meeting time. Therefore the meeting will be Friday morning for New Zealand, Australia, Indonesia and China, Thursday night at midnight in Rome, Thursday evening in the eastern US/Argentina and Thursday afternoon in BC, Canada.</strong></p>\r\n<p>This meeting will focus on finalizing the TPPT responses to member comments on the draft Vapour heat treatment for Bactrocera cucurbitae on Cucumis melo var. reticulatus (2006-110).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>All meeting documents have been posted on the IPP restricted work area for the December meeting (https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=1111049). Please note that the draft ISPM and member comments (which will be posted in the next few days) have been updated after the November meeting, so please refer to the December meeting versions (2011_TPPT_Dec_05 and 2006-110).</p>\r\n<div><strong>The following documents were posted:</strong></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Dec_01: Agenda</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Dec_02: Documents List</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Dec_03: Participants List</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Dec_04: Virtual Meeting Information</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','9227'),(755,'<p><strong>Update 2011-11-11</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p>The Secretariat uploaded the following meeting documents:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_10:&nbsp;Develop guidance for NPPOs as a Guidance document/Checklist: Heat Treatment Forced Air</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><strong>Update 2011-11-02</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Secretariat uploaded the following meeting documents:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_01: Agenda</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_02: Documents List</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_08:&nbsp;Discussion document on guidance for submitting treatments regarding soil and growing media associated with plants</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_09:&nbsp;Develop guidance for NPPOs as a Guidance document/Checklist: Cold Treatments</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Update 2011-10-25</strong></p>\r\n<p>Please register for 2011 TPPT November Virtual Meeting on Wednesday, November 16, 2011 12:00 PM - 2:00 PM CET (Rome, Italy time) at: <a href=\"https://student.gototraining.com/r/1389894085873001984\">https://student.gototraining.com/r/1389894085873001984</a>. After registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training.<span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>The Secretariat uploaded the following meeting documents:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_03: Participants List</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_04: Virtual Meeting Information</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_05: 2012 TPPT Planning</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_06:&nbsp;Steward&rsquo;s Response to Comments: Vapour heat treatment for Bactrocera cucurbitae on Cucumis melo var. reticulatus (2006-110)&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>2011_TPPT_Nov_07:&nbsp;Guidance Document: TPPT Criteria for Treatment Evaluation</li>\r\n<li>2006-110:&nbsp;Draft ISPM: Vapour heat treatment for Bactrocera cucurbitae on Cucumis melo var. reticulatus (2006-110)</li>\r\n</ul>','9226'),(756,'<div><strong>Update 17 October 2011</strong></div>\r\n<div>All meeting documents have been posted, including the meeting slides. Please contact Stephanie (stephanie.dubon@fao.org) or Larry (Larry.Zettler@fao.org) if you have any questions.</div>\r\n<div><br /></div>\r\n<div><strong>Update 14 October 2011 </strong></div>\r\n<div>The next TPPT Virtual Meeting is on Wednesday, October 19, 2011 12:00 PM - 2:00 PM Rome Time.&nbsp;Please register at: <a href=\"https://student.gototraining.com/91w39/register/5007746936608754432\">https://student.gototraining.com/91w39/register/5007746936608754432</a>. After registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training.</div>','9225'),(757,'<p><strong>Update 10 August 2011</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p>Please register for 2011 August TPPT Virtual Meeting on Thursday, August 11, 2011 12:00 PM - 2:00 PM CEST at:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://student.gototraining.com/91w39/register/9218071627290215680\">https://student.gototraining.com/91w39/register/9218071627290215680</a></p>\r\n<p>After registering you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the training.</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>The following documents were posted on 10 August:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Document 01: Agenda</li>\r\n<li>Document 02: Documents List</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><strong>12 July 2011</strong></p>\r\n<p>The proposed date and time for the&nbsp;August 2011 TPPT Virtual Meeting is&nbsp;<strong>11 August, at 12:00 noon Rome Time</strong> (same time as our last meeting). Please contact Stephanie Dubon (<a href=\"mailto:Stephanie.Dubon@fao.org\">Stephanie.Dubon@fao.org</a>) immediately if you have a conflict with this date.</p>\r\n<p>The IPPC Secretariat has posted the meeting documents below. Please check the IPP Restricted area regularly for any additional documents.</p>','9221'),(758,'<p id=\"[object]\" class=\"MsoNorma