e new model will be issued for all consignments as from the 01/01/2014. IPPC official contact points are also informed by e-mail containing sample of the new models(using the address on this portal).',1,2,'2013-12-04 10:36:51',NULL,NULL,0,28,1,4,'2013-12-04 12:00:00','With effect from 1st January 2014 the competent authority (Federal Agency for the Safety of the Food Chain) under the Belgian NPPO has introduced changes to the Belgian model of the Phytosanitary Certificate and Phytosanitary Certificate for re-export. The new model continues to follow the IPPC model and the provisions of ISPM12. The concerned modification of BOX 10 is in accordance to the Belgian Ministerial Decree of 7 May 2013 amending Annexes VI and VII of the Royal Decree of 10 August 2005 establishing the official model of Phytosanitary Certificates. The Federal Agency for the Safety of the Food Chain will issue a fillable PDF template of those models allowing printing on regular paper. Those certificates must be printed in color on a single duplex white page and must contain the signature and official stamp of one of our certifying NPPO officers to be valid. The new model will be issued for all consignments as from the 01/01/2014. IPPC official contact points are also informed by e-mail containing sample of the new models(using the address on this portal).','','2013-12-04 13:22:48','27208'),(700,'',1,'New forms and stamp for Phytosanitary Certificates issued by the NPPO of the Czech Republic','new-forms-and-stamp-for-phytosanitary-certificates-issued-by-the-nppo-of-the-czech-republic',NULL,'\nWith effect  from 1 January 2014, the NPPO of the Czech Republic shall be issuing Phytosanitary Certificate and Phytosanitary Certificate for re-export on new forms. The new stamp will also be officially applied after the above specified date.\n\nThe model of PCs and Stamp remains the same with the exemption of the name of the National Plant Protection Organisation of the Czech Republic which is changed to Central Institute for Supervisiing and Testing in Agriculture.\n\nThe issuance of the Phytosanitary Certificates and Phytosanitary Certificates  for re-export on old forms will end on 31 December 2013.\n\nThe specimens of  new PCs and Stamp are attached for your reference.\n\n \n\n',1,2,'2013-12-17 15:53:55',NULL,NULL,0,68,1,4,'2013-12-17 15:30:00','\nWith effect  from 1 January 2014, the NPPO of the Czech Republic shall be issuing Phytosanitary Certificate and Phytosanitary Certificate for re-export on new forms. The new stamp will also be officially applied after the above specified date.\n\nThe model of PCs and Stamp remains the same with the exemption of the name of the National Plant Protection Organisation of the Czech Republic which is changed to Central Institute for Supervisiing and Testing in Agriculture.\n\nThe issuance of the Phytosanitary Certificates and Phytosanitary Certificates  for re-export on old forms will end on 31 December 2013.\n\nThe specimens of  new PCs and Stamp are attached for your reference.\n\n \n\n','','2013-12-17 15:59:56','27303'),(701,'',1,'Organigram NPPO MNE','organigram-nppo-mne',NULL,'\n \n\nThe Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development is the public administration body in charge of policy making and adoption of regulations in the plant health field.\n\nThe Phytosanitary Directorate was established in 2008, as the single authority responsible for plant health, according to Article 5 of the Law on plant health protection and started to work in 2009.\n\nThe Phytosanitary Directorate is a public administration body in charge of the direct implementation of regulations and administrative and other professional activities and is in charge of co-ordination and contacts related to phytosanitary field.\n\nPhytosanitary Inspection is the part of the Directorate for Inspection Afairs, established in 2011.\n\nPhytosanitary inspection performs inspection supervision over the implementation of the Law on Plant Health.\n\n',1,2,'2013-12-26 10:30:55',NULL,NULL,0,160,1,1,'2013-12-26 10:30:00','\n \n\nThe Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development is the public administration body in charge of policy making and adoption of regulations in the plant health field.\n\nThe Phytosanitary Directorate was established in 2008, as the single authority responsible for plant health, according to Article 5 of the Law on plant health protection and started to work in 2009.\n\nThe Phytosanitary Directorate is a public administration body in charge of the direct implementation of regulations and administrative and other professional activities and is in charge of co-ordination and contacts related to phytosanitary field.\n\nPhytosanitary Inspection is the part of the Directorate for Inspection Afairs, established in 2011.\n\nPhytosanitary inspection performs inspection supervision over the implementation of the Law on Plant Health.\n\n','','2013-12-26 11:01:17','27334'),(702,'',1,'Border Inspection Posts (BIPs) in Montenegro','border-inspection-posts-bips-in-montenegro',NULL,'',1,2,'2013-12-26 11:04:05',NULL,NULL,0,160,1,2,'2013-12-26 11:00:00','','','2013-12-26 11:04:05','27335'),(703,'',1,'Rulebook on phytosanitary measures with List Regulated Harmful Organisms in Montenegro','rulebook-on-phytosanitary-measures-with-list-regulated-harmful-organisms-in-montenegro',NULL,'',1,2,'2013-12-26 11:11:34',NULL,NULL,0,160,1,3,'2013-12-26 11:15:00','','','2013-12-26 11:11:34','27336'),(704,'',1,'Law on plant health protection in Montenegro','law-on-plant-health-protection-in-montenegro',NULL,'',1,2,'2013-12-26 11:24:26',NULL,NULL,0,160,1,4,'2013-12-26 11:15:00','','','2013-12-26 13:35:06','27337'),(705,'',1,'Description de l\'Office de Protection des Végétaux (OPV)','description-de-loffice-de-protection-des-vegetaux-opv',NULL,'\nCréation, Missionss et Fonctionnement de l^^OPV\n\n',1,2,'2014-01-09 10:41:37',NULL,NULL,0,147,1,1,'2014-01-09 10:30:00','\nCréation, Missionss et Fonctionnement de l\'OPV\n\n','','2014-01-09 10:4