 See our media kit page for downloadable PDFs with more information.',1,2,'2014-09-05 08:48:26',NULL,NULL,1,6,307,'1,2','About / Who we are','publicationlibrary',0),(309,'',1,'What we do','what-we-do','','International travel and trade are greater than ever before — and as people and commodities move around the world, organisms that present risks to plants travel with them. Pest introductions and outbreaks cost governments, farmers and consumers billions every year. Once pest species are established their eradication is often impossible, and controlling them takes up a significant percentage of the cost of producing food. The IPPC allows countries to analyze risks to their national plant resources and to use science-based measures to safeguard their cultivated and wild plants. By protecting plant resources from pests and diseases, the IPPC helps: ',1,2,'2014-09-05 08:58:43',NULL,NULL,1,6,307,'1,2','About / What we do','publicationlibrary',0),(310,'',1,'How we do it','how-we-do-it','','',1,2,'2014-09-05 09:03:04',NULL,NULL,1,6,307,'1,2','About / How we do it','publicationlibrary',0),(311,'',1,'Who we work with','who-we-work-with','','IPPC works at a global level with Convention contracting parties, to develop robust and enforceable phytosanitary measures that underpin the parties’ ability to manage pest risks and the environmental, economic and social impacts of plant pests.',1,2,'2014-09-05 09:06:12',NULL,NULL,1,6,307,'1,2','About / Who we work with','publicationlibrary',0),(312,'',1,'Why it Matters','why-it-matters','','',1,2,'2014-09-05 09:09:50',NULL,NULL,1,6,307,'1,2','About / Why it Matters','publicationlibrary',0),(313,'',1,'IPPC and International Trade','ippc-and-international-trade','','',1,2,'2014-09-05 08:29:04',NULL,NULL,1,6,312,'2','About / Why it Matters / IPPC and International Trade','publicationlibrary',0),(314,'',1,'Biosecurity In Food and Agriculture','biosecurity-in-food-and-agriculture','','',1,2,'2014-09-05 08:29:08',NULL,NULL,1,6,312,'2','About / Why it Matters / Biosecurity In Food and Agriculture','publicationlibrary',0),(315,'',1,'Where we work','where-we-work','','The CPM meets annually at FAO headquarters in Rome, Italy. The IPPC Secretariat is also based in Rome, but the activities under the Convention are global in scope. ',1,2,'2014-09-05 09:17:37',NULL,NULL,1,6,307,'1,2','About / Where we work','publicationlibrary',0),(316,'',1,'History of the IPPC','history-of-the-ippc','','The concept of international plant protection began in 1881, when five countries signed an agreement to control the spread of grape phylloxera, a North American aphid that was accidentally introduced into Europe around 1865 and that subsequently devastated much of Europe’s grape-growing regions. ',1,2,'2014-09-05 09:22:40',NULL,NULL,1,6,307,'1,2','About / History of the IPPC','publicationlibrary',0),(317,'',1,'The 1997 Revision of the International Plant Protection Convention','the-1997-revision-of-the-international-plant-protection-convention','','',1,2,'2014-09-05 08:29:31',NULL,NULL,1,6,316,'2','About / History of the IPPC / The 1997 Revision of the International Plant Protection Convention','publicationlibrary',0),(318,'',1,'Entry into force','entry-into-force','','The New Revised Text of the IPPC (1997) entered into force on 2 October 2005 (the thirtieth day after it was accepted by two-thirds of the contracting parties to the IPPC - see Article XXI.4 of the New Revised Text). Entry into force of the New Revised Text applies to all contracting parties, including those that had not accepted the new revised text at the time of entry into force.',1,2,'2014-09-05 08:29:36',NULL,NULL,1,6,316,'2','About / History of the IPPC / Entry into force','publicationlibrary',0),(319,'',1,'Convention, model instruments and related information','convention,-model-instruments-and-related-information',NULL,'Convention, model instruments and related information',1,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,6,307,'1,2','Convention, model instruments and related info